commentary_text: real loosener, full on the off stump, blocked towards point with no foot movement
similar delivery, kept out with more of a forward stride
more of a length ball that allows Rogers to play from the crease, hint of inswing, he pushes up on the on side
short length and it doesn't get up anywhere near where Rogers thought it might, he wears it on the shoulder and the ball rolls up his sweater
good length wide of off stump to leave alone, steady carry through but it looks pretty easy-paced
tighter line and Rogers blocks it back to the bowler from the crease
length on middle and off, blocked firmly up towards mid-off
worked from a straighter line, again on a decent length, to square leg
fuller and Warner asked to come forward to block up towards mid-on, nice pace, 86mph
touch straighter and Warner able to tuck to the left of the debutant Stokes at forward square leg and the innings is underway
nice this, sliding past the outside edge with Rogers pressing forward just outside off, hint of away movement there
touch wider and Rogers able to leave but a nice start from Broad
full on off stump, a flicked drive into the covers, not timed and extra cover fields
this time gets the drive through, just a touch wide from Anderson and Warner able to flash the hands at it and got plenty of bat on it through cover point

nipping back a little and Warner caught on the crease, big cry for lbw, not out given, they briefly discuss the review but decide against it because the ball pitched just outside leg and was probably too high n'all
off stump line, blocked towards point from the crease
strong press forward on middle and forces wide of mid-on for a quick couple
good length a foot wide of off stump and left alone
full length on off stump, Rogers forward to drive without timing to mid-off
slightly shorter length and slightly straighter too, dropped down in front of point and they steal a single
flashing cut stroke in the air but finds the gap backward of point, just a hint of width and all the encouragement Warner needed, risky though, it wasn't right out there, or indeed that short
fuller on the stumps, blocked up on the on side
length delivery on middle, Warner tucks from the crease into midwicket, Stokes comes to his right to field
full of length and driven down the ground, not perfectly timed and the 90 yard boundary down the ground is too much for this stroke
full length on the stumps and Warner clips through midwicket for a couple, bright and breezy opening for Davey W as his cousins call him
more runs, this time through gully, a forward press comes off a thick outside edge and squirts past a diving Ian Bell
firm drive back up the wicket and Anderson gets down well with a right boot to save runs, the delivery wasn't right up there to drive but Warner went after it on the front foot
straighter line and flicked down to long leg
nervy forward prod on the stumps, runs off a thick outside edge, along the ground, into the gully
a carefully considered forward press, dropped into the covers but no quickie available
overpitched outside off and a sumptuous drive back up past the bowler, Warner is on for a ton before lunch, best piece of timing so far
length on off stump, blocked from the crease into the covers
pulled from a length no where near short enough to do so, hurried and mistimed off high on the bat to square leg
plays a more sensible stroke this time, tucking into the gap at midwicket, enough for a single
length ball two feet wide of off stump, allowed past the bat
fuller length and driven from just outside off to mid-on
around the wicket, full length and runs off the thigh pad to the wicketkeeper
touch shorter, clipped with the angle to square leg
off stump on a length, blocked from the crease back to the bowler
fuller length, angled in and Warner tucks with the degrees down to long leg
back over to Rogers, who comes forward on off stump and defends with the inner half of the bat towards midwicket
84mph, a pleasant press down the ground from just outside off stump and I mentioned the long boundaries, they can run four here before Pietersen returns
length on the stumps and Warner has bags of time to block around the off stick from the crease
by contrast, Warner a touch surprised here in keeping out a ball on off stump that was a little fuller than he expected
just back in length and Warner is onto it in a flash to pull through midwicket, short square fences and that's four
fuller length on off stump, blocked forward
decent length again, kept out back up towards the bowler

got him! Poor stroke, clipped straight to point. Just short of a length and Warner has picked out Carberry square on the off side. He lives and dies by the sword and in trying to be uber-aggressive again, Warner pops up an easy catch with a flicked back-foot drive. The delivery might have just stopped in the wicket a little, and it actually just nipped away a touch, it certainly didn't come on as Warner was hoping. Important strike for England after leaking a few runs early doors
dismissed_batsman_text: DA Warner c Carberry b Broad 29 (36m 32b 4x4 0x6) SR: 90.62

commentary_text: forcing stroke off the back foot just in front of point, Carberry does the fielding again
bumper, well directed and easily ducked
touch straight and clipped down to Panesar stationed at long leg
aha a right hander, full length outside off and left alone
full length angled in towards off stump, Watson forward to block up the wicket
length ball too close to the pads, Watson tucks it in front of midwicket and they take a single
full length arrowed at the biggest pads in world cricket, Watto gets the willow down in time in front of off stump
fuller length, again at the stumps, driven firmly to the straight mid-on
full length again, Watson strides out, punishing the turf with his huge boots, and blocks into the covers
more of a good length this time, dropped in front of point, Watson immediately turns down the single that Rogers was keener for
good length around off stump, patted back to the bowler on the front dog
straighter line on a good length, blocked coming forward into midwicket
just back of a length on a straight line, dropped into square leg and they get a single to the right of Stokes
forward just outside off stump and pressed into the covers
Watson gets a run immediately after the break with a clip off his pads to square leg
Anderson asks the question for lbw, quite vociferously, but that was clearly pitching outside leg. Turned down and no question of a review from England
Rogers goes for the cover drive but can't beat the field
down leg side to end the over, Rogers tries to pick up some easy runs with a glance but he can't get any bat on ball
straight ball to start, Watson defends to the leg side
defensive again from Watson, a thickish edge runs along the ground towards gully
probing outside off, and Watson gives it the full face of the bat
crunching drive from Watson, just leans into a half-volley outside off and the timing is super, it beats mid-off and runs away to the boundary
slower ball and well wide of off, but Watson picks it and waits for his square drive, all he had to do was find the gap between point and cover, and he does it without any problem
on middle and leg now and Watson defends
swinging down leg and nothing makes contact with that on its way through to Prior
straighter line from Anderson and Rogers drives back past the bowler but not past mid-on
oh, almost a false shot! Rogers gets one on middle and off and spoons it up uncontrolled on the leg side, there is a short catching midwicket in place but this lobs too straight for him
pushed away to the off side safely
defended solidly from the off stump now
bouncer to finish the over, Rogers is not interested at this stage of his innings and ducks under it
Watson uses his feet immediately to get to the pitch of the ball and defend
again Watson comes out and dead-bats the ball just outside off
Swann goes fuller this time, almost a low yorker length, but Watson can't get his drive past the bowler
more movement of the feet, Watson doesn't always play this way, but he's come out of the crease to meet the ball again
straighter ball now and turns just a touch, Watson defends

too full to tell if there's much spin at this stage, as Watson again takes a couple of small steps out and pushes it back to the bowler, he wants to get on top of Swann but hasn't been able to in this first over
short of a length from Anderson, who is still around the wicket, and Rogers defends
Anderson angles it in just outside off, Rogers defends
length on off stump, blocked in the crease up the wicket
bumper, easily ducked and it went through pretty slowly
punching drive through cover point, his best stroke, let a length ball come to him just outside off and guided it away to the rope
fuller and straighter, pushed up to mid-on
flicked into the on side having taken a step down, fielded by Cook at midwicket
another step down the wicket and a flick this time to deep mid-on for an easy single, not quite long-on that fielder
length ball that Rogers tries to drive off the back foot, it's so slow to him and he mistimes a stroke into the covers
pushed forward and finds the gap at point, beautiful timing and it races for four, fine stroke off the front foot
press from a foot outside off to backward point, playing with the turn
straighter line and Rogers comes forward to block around middle and off this time
length ball on middle stump, forward defence up towards mid-on
fuller and a flourishing drive to mid-on this time
hint of movement in towards the right hander as Watson leaves a length ball that started a foot and a half outside off
straighter line and Watson plays a forward defence around middle and off
full length outside off, for a moment I thought Watson was looking to cover drive but he left it in the end
too straight and tucked to Panesar at deep-backward square leg
not one ball has Watson played from the crease to Swann so far, skips down again and gets it off low on the bat to deep mid-on
a drive from just outside off, squirts off a thick outside edge behind point and they take a couple, even Rogers isn't going to block Swann
tossed up on off stump, carefully pushed to cover
straighter line and blocked up the wicket
forward on off stump, pushed to extra cover
touch fuller and navigates a drive just wide enough of Carberry at cover point for a single
length ball on off stump, blocked up the wicket from the crease
full on the stumps, pushed firmly to midwicket
back of a length, Rogers up on his toes to dab it down into the off side
bumper, ducked, simple
back of a length on off stump, Rogers dabbing towards point
full now on off stump, driven gently to cover
guess what, a step down the track and a flick for one to the deep mid-on
length on off stump, carefully blocked to silly point's right
Rogers tries to advance and squeezes a delivery to midwicket that's well fielded
bad line, tickled fine and they get three, Swann will be annoyed with that loose delivery
nicely flighted just outside off, Watson PLAYS FROM THE CREASE!! and defends in front of short leg
big stride out to this and flicks wide of midwicket for a couple, nicely tucked away
tossed up just outside off, blocked forward to cover
length ball that Rogers hangs back to just outside off and plays to cover
played off the back foot again from just outside off, tucked to cover
forward this time, again just outside off, blocked back up to the bowler
step down the wicket and flicked with the turn to midwicket
a gentle press to a full ball in the direction of mid-on and Rogers immediately calls a quick single
looked like the arm ball, blocked with the inner half of the bat just outside off stump
hangs back and punches to point
back on the off stump and dropping this in front of silly point
forward outside off stump and gets a genuine outside edge that runs backward of point
forward to quite a flat delivery just outside off, blocked
reaches outside off and presses into the covers
off stump defensive forward block
tossed up wide of the off stick, Rogers leaving alone covering his stumps
up the wicket he comes and fends outside off, it bounces a little and takes the glove, bouncing in front of short leg
fuller length and shovelled to cover
touch short and forced away square beating Carberry's dive, they get back for two
a step down the track and tries to work this to leg, only gets as far as silly point
covering up and blocking towards the bowler
a shimmy down and flick to the deeper man at mid-on
two slips now, a little turn and Rogers follows it and plays in front of Cook off the back foot
fuller length and squeezed out on the off side
straighter line now and rolled up the wicket
good length and Rogers is well forward blocking back to the bowler
miserable long hop but Watson can only power it as far as mid-off's right hand for just a single
back on the stumps and pushed into the covers
little short again, cut but only finds Carberry who dives and saves well to his right
off stump line, Rogers back again dabbed into the off side
tries to step down and flick to leg, does so but only as far as mid-on
left alone outside off stump, Rogers a little tied down here
nicely floated up just outside off, forward and blocked up the wicket
forward again, this time more carefully to defend from off towards leg
one step down and blocking with bat and pad together up the wicket
flat delivery a foot outside off, just blocked again into the covers
touch shorter, Watson back and tucking to midwicket
a shimmy down and whacked past mid-off, firm stroke and something that was coming really, nicely struck
nice drive to a floated delivery a foot outside off, timed reasonably well through the covers
forward just outside off to block up the wicket
tucked with the turn towards midwicket from just outside off stump

huge cry for lbw as Rogers plays across the line, not out give but England review. Was this turning down? No. Is it too high? He was hit below the knee roll. No bat involved either. But Hawk Eye has it taking a large slice of leg stump but not more than 50% so it stays with Dharmasena
just back of a length and prodded into the covers
similar back foot stroke, this time played more firmly to cover
flat on off stump, Watson forward and blocked just in front of short leg
forward block again just outside off stump
back and late cuts, nicely guided behind point and they take a couple
flicked with the turn through square leg to a delivery that was just a touch short
full delivery, Rogers blocks back up the wicket
full on middle and leg, clipped to midwicket who gets down well
touch short, cut hard but Pietersen is down well at point to make the save, Hugo Lloris-esque
forward on off stump blocking back up to the bowler
firm drive back to the bowler from off stump, Panesar does enough to save any runs
Watson back to cut and finds Pietersen again at point
cuts again and this time finds the gap at extra cover to bring the fifty partnership up, poor ball that
floated up on off stump and driven firmly to mid-on
forward just outside off and dabbed to cover
floated up and Rogers enticed to drive and does so pleasantly through cover, good timing
blocking on off stump again, Bell the fielder at silly point
straight line and Rogers bats it back up the wicket
same again, defensive push to the bowler
back foot stroke in the direction of cover
full toss on middle and leg, flicked out to a man who is out at cow corner for Panesar
too short and cut for four, the pressure just being released here
floated up and rolled back to the bowler
full just outside off, punched back to the bowler
just back in length, played off the back foot to cover
flat delivery on off stump and Rogers pushes carefully back to the bowler
83mph, length just outside off, Watson leaves alone
touch overpitched and driven very nicely through extra cover, lovely stroke
straighter line and a much better length, tucked to midwicket
good length on the stumps, Watson forward not particularly convincingly and keep it out to cover
forward to a good length ball just outside off, blocked to cover, 87mph that, fastest ball of the day
good off stump line and Watson blocks a good length ball
full straight delivery is blocked
pushed carefully to cover and finds the gap for a single
off stump on a length, Watson taps it up the wicket
big stride up the wicket but Watto just blocks it back to the bowler
good line and length, Watson plays with the inner half of the bat in front of short leg
fuller and dug out to mid-off
length ball just outside off stump, played from the crease to cover
good length on off stump, Rogers hangs back and plays back to the bowler
just back in length a few inches outside off stump, forced into the covers
played from the crease when he might have been forward, gets it towards point from just outside off
nudged again square on the off side off the back foot
throws in the bumper and Rogers ducks successfully
touch short allows Watson to hang back and cut hard, finds point
floated up and Watson leaves it alone, quite tight to the off stump that, have to say good judgement
firm drive to mid-on coming forward
forward trying to get out to Panesar, ends up blocking towards short leg
quicker, flat ball nearly catches Watson out, he jams the bat down to cover his stumps
big stride forward and runs it past Bell but not far enough for a single
full and driveable but only to cover, mistimed
length ball on off stump, blocked on the stumps
length ball sliding across the off stump, Rogers leaves it alone
length delivery again and a hint of shape takes the inside edge of Rogers's defensive stroke aimed at the off side
much fuller and blocked firmly back up towards the bowler
length ball down the leg side, Rogers flicks at it and misses
forward on off stump and Watson unsure where to defend coming forward
23rd dot ball in a row to Watson, who pats it back up the wicket from off stump
and Watson goes for a release and whacks a delivery over the bowler's head for six, powerful stroke, got right to the pitch of the ball and it's a long way to carry that straight rope
shuffle across the in crease and cut hard but only to Pietersen at point
blocking on off stump again now
angled in from wider on the crease, another forward defence on the stumps
length on off stump, tucked into the covers from the crease
slightly shorter ball and straighter, forced a little jumpy to square leg
fuller on off stump, Rogers forward pressing into the covers
back of a length, Rogers tries to force off the back foot but gets cramped up and gets it off high on the bat to point
full on leg stump and Rogers tucks it nicely through midwicket, just loosing his line there Stokes
better length and on a better line, just blocking is Rogers
Watson back on his stumps and keeps out a flat delivery
forward on off and pressed towards the bowler
back and creates a little room for himself, punched to extra cover
gentle drive towards cover, finds the fielder
forward press back to the bowler
another press back to the bowler
back of a length just outside off stump, dabbed into the covers
almost an identical delivery and stroke
too wide and this is cut well for four, nicely put away
goes for a pull and is there way to soon and misses, brief cry from behind the stumps but the bowler wasn't interested
low full toss that Rogers pokes to cover point

commentary_short_text: Stokes to Rogers, (no ball) FOUR runs
commentary_text: another cut for, just a bit of width for Rogers to work with and Stokes clipped the bowler's end stumps and that is now a no-ball for 'Finning' or 'Smithing' as it should be dubbed
back of a length and a much better line, pushed into the covers
back and patting to cover from just outside off
forward to this, pushing up the wicket
right back on his stumps to late cut, nearly got caught out by an arm ball that skidded through, manages to force it away backward of point for a couple
cut and finds the gap between point and cover
forward just outside off, pats this back to the bowler
back now and waits for the gentle turn to come to him, knocks it into the covers
forward to a full length ball on off stump, finds mid-on
full delivery at the pad, flicked firmly to midwicket
length delivery on off stump, Watson blocks it from the crease
forward to a ball full of a length an inch outside off, finds cover
full delivery angled in, Watson is forward and driving firmly to mid-on
firm flick to short midwicket where Ian Bell makes a nice save
Rogers is beaten outside off and there's a bit of excitement but Prior doesn't glove the ball, although Rogers was safely in his ground in any case
again Rogers is beaten outside off, and again Prior doesn't take it - this time it bounces away for a couple of byes
solidly defended this time
prodded back down the pitch
some turn in from outside off, Rogers stands and defends
Rogers uses the feet this time and clips the ball towards mid-on, gets through for a quick single to take him within one run of fifty
Broad angles it across Rogers with plenty of men forming a ring on the off side, Rogers isn't tempted to play
fuller and straighter, Rogers leans into a drive but can't beat mid-off
lovely shot from Rogers to bring up his half-century, he pounces on one just a touch short and cuts between the fielders to find a boundary forward of point
defended away solidly
shorter this time and Rogers goes the cut again, but this one really gets up and the extra pace and bounce beats Rogers, fortunately for him, because that could easily have turned into an edge behind
probing outside off and Rogers defends
Panesar is around the wicket to Watson, he tosses it up outside off and Watson leans out to defend
tossed up again and just a bit of turn, Watson defends
drifting in towards leg now and again Watson just pushes it away defensively
well flighted and just straightening on the stumps, Watson is back in his crease and defends again
Watson leans out again to push it back to the bowler
again Watson watches closely and defends
Broad tempts Rogers outside off, he obliges with a drive that doesn't beat cover
strays onto the pads now and Rogers clips it away to fine leg
Watson gets one on his hip area as well, he also gets a single away through square leg

Broad is trying to mix things up a little, bangs it in short and accurate, Rogers goes for the hook and takes his eyes off the ball but does manage to get it down into the ground and away to deep square
defended off the back foot
poor delivery this time, swinging down leg and Watson gets a tickle on that to pick up a boundary to fine leg
curves in and Rogers defends
drifting in towards the stumps, Rogers dead-bats it
drifting again, but too far down leg, and with a stacked off-side field it allows Rogers to work it along the ground through a big gap at square leg
prods forward to defend
quicker from Swann and Rogers goes back into his crease to defend from leg stump
watchful from Rogers, he is happy to just see Swann off
defended away to the off side

oh, beaten outside off! It almost sounded like an edge from Watson, but as it was a slower ball it faded before it got to Prior. Daylight between bat and ball in any case, but the movement away did for Watson
pushed away defensively this time
goes for the shorter ball now, Watson pulls it away through square
Rogers defends safely to the leg side

good placement from Rogers, he gets a wider one from Broad and cuts behind point, getting it just wide of the fielder and picks up another boundary. Rogers looks very solid against the pace here, a little less so against spin
Watson gets his half-century now with a single through midwicket, just closes the face and works it safely away through the gap
tossed up on off stump, Rogers defends
plenty of flight for Swann, not a huge amount of turn - Rogers defends
Rogers goes back into his crease to defend a straight one
drifting in towards off again, Rogers leans out to defend
again, not much turn there for Swann, again Rogers bunts it back down the pitch
straight ball to start with and Watson gives it the full face, drives it back at Anderson, who gets some part of his body on it to prevent any runs
probing outside off and Watson defends
short of a length now and Anderson clips it to midwicket
a touch of width outside off, Watson goes the late cut but it's straight to gully on the bounce
pushes off the back foot to cover
Watson drives down the ground, but mid-on is there to cut it off
defended back down the pitch
nudged away to leg
yorker length and Rogers works it to leg
on the back foot, Rogers just pushes tamely to cover, not looking to hit it too hard
Rogers isn't interested in going after Swann, just goes back into his crease to defend
well, now Rogers does in fact go after Swann! It's with a sweep, and a well-controlled one at that. Goes all the way along the ground to the boundary. Top shot, that
Anderson probes outside off stump, Watson defends outside off stump

one run? Two runs? Run out? In the end it's just one - Watson worked it to midwicket and they took a quick single, the throw hit the stumps at the striker's end and the ricochet through cover tempted the batsmen to take an overthrow, they started to do so and then decided against it.
lovely shot, Rogers just places this drive through cover, all the way along the ground, really good stroke from Rogers
Rogers gets this one edgily away towards third man, doesn't quite pick up a boundary but keeps his score ticking over
swinging down leg now and only half a shout for lbw from Anderson, that was certainly missing

Anderson has done it! And with a super return catch, great reflexes. Watson has gone for the big straight drive but this ball bounces more than he expects, so it comes off higher on the bat and stays in the air long enough for Anderson to grasp it with both hands at ankle height. Very good catch
dismissed_batsman_text: SR Watson c & b Anderson 51 (160m 119b 6x4 1x6) SR: 42.85

commentary_text: punched away to cover
drifting down leg and Rogers defends
defended away again
tossed up on the stumps and Rogers defends carefully

another wicket! Rogers is gone! Two in two overs after nothing seemed to be happening for them, Swann gets one to turn a bit more from short of a length, Rogers dabs at it as if trying to push to cover and his edge is taken by Prior - Rogers was walking, didn't even wait for the umpire to give him out. Well, what a huge couple of overs for England
dismissed_batsman_text: CJL Rogers c †Prior b Swann 72 (199m 167b 11x4 0x6) SR: 43.11

commentary_text: bad ball, Swann came around the wicket and skewed this down leg, it's beaten everyone and runs away for byes
Smith defends back down the pitch
again Smith defends this watchfully
Anderson probes outside off again, Smith defends again
Anderson getting just a touch of reverse, Smith defends from off stump
tailing in a little once more, Smith clips it to midwicket
Smith feeling plenty of bat on ball here, solidly defends it back down the pitch
Clarke leans forward to defend
uses his feet nicely here and drives confidently but mid-on gets across to stop it
tossed up on the stumps, just straightens enough and Clarke defends edgily
beaten outside off! Oh, Panesar could cause problems here - Clarke prods at one that turns away and very narrowly beats the outside edge. A shout from Prior but no edge
drifting down leg and Clarke can't quite find the gap
quicker and flatter, Panesar brings the length back and Clarke shimmies forward to defend
Anderson continues to probe outside off, the fidgety Steve Smith defends and then moves away for his routine of twitches
a hint of swing in, Smith leaves it alone
crunched away off the back foot and Smith can't find the gap because Carberry hurls himself to his left to save a boundary
Smith gets off the mark now with a clip through the leg side
Clarke also gets off the mark as Anderson swings it - yes, swing - down leg and it's glanced to the boundary
on the stumps now and Clarke defends - and it's a no-ball for over-stepping
tickled away behind square leg this time
Clarke tries to use the feet to Panesar, defends it back to the bowler
Panesar drifts it towards leg, Clarke defends
Clarke leans out to defend once more
too short this time from Panesar, and a rare bad ball gets crunched away through point for a boundary. Clarke absolutely pounced on that
a little movement forwards from Clarke and he defends again
from the crease, Clarke defends a straight and fullish ball
right on target from Anderson, and Smith defends
banged in on the hips now and all Smith has to do is get some bat on this, which he does, and it runs away for a boundary to fine leg
again short of a length and this time Smith manages to get it away to square leg
pushed away towards the leg side
short of a length and swinging in, Clarke leaves it alone outside off
solidly defended towards the off side
drifting in towards middle and leg from around the wicket, Smith goes back to defend
leans out to push this one to silly point

Panesar strikes! Beautiful delivery, the turn away from the right-handers has done the job. Smith has played from the crease and defended with far from a straight bat - it was angled horribly - and the ball turns past it to clip the off stump. Lovely ball, poor shot, and England are on top
dismissed_batsman_text: SPD Smith  b Panesar 6 (22m 17b 1x4 0x6) SR: 35.29

commentary_text: forward on the stumps blocking in front of silly point
driven with the turn to where Stokes dives and saves at cover
awful delivery, dragged down and wide, Kerrigan-esque if you may, Bailey cuts but didn't time it perfectly but is away
forward on off stump to block, slightly on the walk
full of length, two feet wide of off stump, left alone
full length again, this time close enough to make Clarke play, blocking just outside the off stump
similar defensive stroke, lets this come to him a bit more does Clarke and plays it out to backward point
full delivery, tails in a little, Clarke drives and finds mid-off
tight off stump line, a forward defence completes a maiden
floated up on off stump, blocked on the front foot up the wicket
dropped short and hammered to the cover fence, sent down a few of those today has Monty, a right old long hop
now overcompensates and bowls a full toss which is slapped to mid-off
staying leg side of the bowling all the time here Bailey, runs this out to cover
and again, blocking with the spin, to silly point here
forward on off stump, ran into the covers
full length on off stump, Clarke pushes firmly up the wicket where the bowler fields
full again and this shapes away just a little, Clarke drives off low on the bat to mid-off
a cry of 'no' from Anderson as he overpitches on middle and leg and gets clipped through midwicket, well timed
a decent stride out to block firmly into the covers, Bailey has to be quick coming through for the single
played from the crease and dabbed in front of point
nicely bowled, beats the outside edge with Bailey trying to fend from the crease
step down the wicket and a flick to deep midwicket
fired in short again and Bailey helps himself again, this time on the pull backward of midwicket
forward press, bounces a little and takes the higher part of the bat to backward point
leg stump line, Bailey smothers it and runs it back to the bowler
forward on middle and leg, defended back to the bowler
back on middle and off, defended in front of silly point
slower delivery in the blockhole, dug out to point
length delivery and blocked from the crease to midwicket
slightly shorter in length, Clarke stands in front of off stump and dead pans this
a cracking delivery, Clarke royally beaten on the outside edge, brief cry for lbw but definitely no edge, fine delivery that tailed in though on a great length
fuller ball on the stumps, played firmly to mid-on
excellent from Anderson again, length ball angled in towards middle and off, kept out trying to get forward
down the track and a slap back to the bowler and I think Panesar has shelled a firm chance indeed he has, a chance at knee height to his right hand side, he got both hands there but couldn't cling on
shimmys down and plays on the bounce back to the bowler
blocked on the front foot around middle and off
tries to hang back and cut but finds point
driven firmly from off stump with the spin into Cook at silly point
shifts back in the crease and works in front of square leg for a quick single
very full just outside off, dug out to mid-off
full length and dabbed from the crease towards point
forward on off stump, pressing this back to the bowler
a cry for caught behind as Bailey came forward and played (and missed) just outside off, cry from behind the wicket mainly but Bailey has hit his pad, nicely bowled though
fuller and slightly wider, Bailey forward to play to cover
full angled in towards the stumps, a gentle on-drive brings three down the ground, reasonably timed
tossed up outside off, met on the full and slapped to cover
good length on off stump, played with the turn in front of slip
a skip down the track and lifts this over the bowler's head, positive play and gets the lofted drive away nicely, timed it perfectly
steps down again and this time plays towards mid-off and they scramble a single
rocks back and cuts hard, half-saved by point and they run on the fumble
driven gently from middle and leg to mid-off
another fine delivery that slides past the outside edge, Clarke here playing forward on off stump and getting done by a bit of movement
similar line, this time Clarke came out to meet it a bit better and got it back to the bowler
another good stride in forward, plays back to the bowler again
good length on off stump, Clarke squirts it towards backward point
touch straighter line allowing Clarke to move this wide enough of midwicket for a quick single
full on the stumps, punched to mid-on
around the wicket, played with the turn out to deep-backward square leg off the back foot
step down the track and clipped out to long on
comes down the wicket and tries to flick into a leg side gap, doesn't find one
forward on off stump, blocking up the wicket
blocked with bat and pad together, some turn takes inside edge and pad and almost presents a chance to short leg
blocked more comfortably in front of short leg this time
just short of a good length, Bailey blocks from the crease towards point
for some reason tries to pull this, it wasn't nearly short enough, takes bottom edge into thigh pad and a good job too, could have been stumps
nice-looking front foot drive finds mid-off
forward to a good length ball a foot outside off, dropped into the covers too close to the fielder for a single
very full and driven with good timing but picks out cover
just short of a length around off stump, blocked from the crease and a maiden

a step down the wicket and flicked to midwicket in the air, Root dives and drops the chance he was at full stretch but got both hands to it and it simply burst through, would have been an outstanding grab though
blocked around middle coming foreward
turned with the spin and evades leg slip, Panesar has to run around from deep-backward square leg
turned with the spin to Bell at short leg who makes a good save
full on off stump, driven firmly to where mid-off can come and field
Clarke forever trying to get up the wicket, blocks this after a shimmy down
full delivery just outside off, played to Carberry at point
pulled away, not exactly in control of the stroke but kept down and gets a single to deep square
forward just outside off and dropped behind point, Clarke calls a sharp single
full delivery tails in a little, Bailey keeps it out towards midwicket
full on the off stump, Bailey drives and, on the bounce, Broad fields
back in length and the angle is such that Bailey can whip this wide of midwicket
driven back to the bowler, Swann gets a flick onto the stumps, is Clarke short here? No safely back
tossed up and left alone outside off stump
a step down the pitch and driven into the non striker
lovely bowling, drift in that deceives Bailey and he drives at a ball on the wrong line and gets a thick inside edge between himself and the stumps
more successful drive down the ground to long on
Bailey replicates the trick to the deep fielder
length just outside off stump, Bailey blocks on the crease
fuller ball and driven nicely but Stokes saves well off his own bowling
wide delivery swung at and missed and for a moment I thought he'd nicked it
carefully pushed off the back foot into the covers and they get a quick single
length delivery a foot outside off, Clarke is standing tall in the crease playing out towards point
firm back foot drive to a ball a touch shorter in length, finds point
step down the wicket and an easy single to long on, perhaps too easy
touch short and an easy single available with a flick through midwicket from a straight line
step down the track and kicked away
tries to come down again and gets in a bit of a tangle trying to kick it away again
quicker and straighter, flicked off the stumps to midwicket
back and pushing firmly into the cover from off stump
straight on the stumps, Clarke defends

pushed away to cover point, Carberry runs around and collects, his throw at the non-striker's end misses - not that there was any chance of a run-out - and there's overthrows as Broad at mid-on fails to collect backing up
defended away to the leg side
shortish, but no real pace, and it's swivelled away via a pull to deep square leg
short of a length outside off, Clarke punches off the back foot to point
on the stumps, and Clarke defends with a straight bat
Bailey advances to Swann, then just nudges it to leg
tries to force this one from leg stump through the on-side but short midwicket cuts it off
short ball and it stays a little low, but well outside off and Bailey is able to cut it to point, they get a single on a misfield
on the pads, Clarke can't get it away
a touch too short, Clarke's forward and back foot movement perhaps just throwing Swann a bit, and it's pulled confidently through square leg

'gaaaaaah!' comes the shout from Prior - probably doesn't qualify as asking the umpire 'how's that?', but anyway not much interest from anyone else as Clarke tries to whip this to leg and it it lobs off his pad to the off side. It was well outside leg with Swann around the wicket
banged in short by Stokes but his pace isn't worrying Bailey, who hooks it into the turf and straight to square leg
pushed away to the off side
Stokes probes outside off at 133.8kph, Bailey defends

Bailey has whipped this pull right off the middle of the bat, and it safely runs away for four. Mind you, deep midwicket wasn't far away and that ball sailed in the air nearly all the way - he couldn't have afforded to place that any further square or he'd have been in trouble. It wasn't too short a ball, just a muscular pull from Bailey
defended away safely
Stokes tries for another bouncer but it's well down leg and Bailey leaves it alone
on the pads and Clarke whips it safely through square leg

lovely use of the feet here from Bailey, he gets almost to the pitch of this and lofts Swann back over his head - it didn't clear Swann's outstretched arms by a lot, but enough, and it bounces away for four. Good confident stuff from Bailey before the new ball arrives
clipped away through square leg as this one turns down leg
tossed up on middle and leg, Clarke closes the face down on this one and pushes it to short leg
goes back to defend outside off
flicked towards midwicket but can't find the gap
defended away to the off side
Bailey goes back to defend again
Bailey leans forward and smothers any spin

gosh, Bailey looks confident going down the ground against both spinners - this has cleared the long-off rope! He's used his feet and hit with the spin, over mid-off and followed through nicely, just a good clean hit, that
pushed away to off now
tucked away to midwicket for a single
Anderson with the old ball probes outside off, it's left alone
dead-straight is the bat of Michael Clarke, he defends a dead-straight delivery
opens the face now to push to point but can't beat Carberry
a bit of extra bounce from short of a length, Clarke glides it away behind point for some runs

poor delivery, swinging down leg, but what a good shot from Clarke to take advantage of it, just lifts it off his pads and it absolutely flies through square leg in the air, safely, and bounces over the rope
solidly defended by Clarke as Anderson finds a straighter line
defended away to the off side

what a way to bring up a half-century! And it's George Bailey's first in Test cricket, he has pounced on a shortish ball from Broad and monstered it over the short square boundary, cleared the rope safely
yorker to follow up and it's defended
on the pads now and it's clipped away to leg
Clarke watches this one through outside off, no swing there for Broad
straight-bat defence to finish the over
fullish length and Bailey defends
fullish again and perhaps moving away a touch, and Bailey drives to cover
solidly defended on off
defended away safely again
on the back foot now Bailey defends
pushed away towards point and can't find the gap
banged in short by Broad, and Clarke lets it through to Prior
nudged away towards point, can't find the gap
Broad probes outside off at 134.9kph, Clarke drives it away to point
on the hips now and Clarke works it behind square leg
good bouncer this time, quick enough and straight enough to have Bailey swaying a bit, but he gets safely under it
on the back foot, Bailey defends
solid straight-bat defence again
Anderson attacks the stumps, making Clarke play, and he defends
on the back foot, Clarke punches to cover
nudged away to the leg side, can't find a gap
Clarke jumps back into his crease to defend
crunchy shot off the back foot but Clarke can't find the gap at cover
banged in short and this one sails unmolested through to Prior
defended away towards the leg side

super catch! Bailey is gone, and it's the Broad bouncer that does the job. Bailey went for the hook, it flew off the bat but in the air, and Swann at square leg hurls himself up and to his right, clasps the ball safely and Bailey's entertaining innings has come to an end
dismissed_batsman_text: GJ Bailey c Swann b Broad 53 (111m 93b 4x4 3x6) SR: 56.98

commentary_text: Haddin defends to the off side
Broad bangs it in short of a length and Haddin jumps back to defend
short outside off but this one doesn't get up enough to worry Haddin, who is off the mark with a pull through mid-on
shortish and turning away, it's cut through point
drifting onto off stump, it's defended
Panesar from around the wicket drifts it in to the middle-stump line, it straightens and Haddin's prod gets a thickish edge away through gully
Clarke uses his feet to Panesar, just pushes it to leg
straight bat from Clarke as he leans forward from the crease
uses the feet this time and clips through midwicket, a single turns into two as Pietersen misfields
Broad steams in and attacks the stumps, Haddin defends with a straight bat
Broad has almost done it again, but this time the midwicket can't get his hand to it! A shortish ball from Broad and Haddin pulls it hard, and only marginally high of the diving midwicket

big lbw appeal from England! Marais Erasmus says not out, but England were confident and after a lengthy group discussion ask for a review. There was no bat involved, but it has hit high on the flap of Haddin's pad, which means height is an issue. And the replays confirm that height is the problem - that was missing. Haddin survives!
bouncer to follow up, but it's too high to make Haddin play
carbon copy, another bouncer on middle and leg, but Haddin ducks under it
Haddin is solid in defence from off stump now
flicked away through leg side
defended to the off side
flighted by Panesar and this turns, but Haddin goes back and cuts, though he can't beat the field
much the same again, but again Haddin can only pick out the man at cover point
fullish on leg, Haddin defends

dropped! Another missed opportunity for England! Oh dear, oh dear, oh dear - it's Michael Carberry at backward point, and you'd have to say this is a bit of a sitter. Haddin has rocked back to cut, it flies at chest height to Carberry but bounces out of his hands, and even could have dived for it for a second bite, but couldn't grab it there either.
Clarke goes for the pull now and it skews off his bottom edge away through square leg
left alone outside off
Broad goes the bouncer again, he's really banging it in here, and Haddin goes the hook and keeps it down enough to be safe
solidly defended as Broad attacks the stumps
banged in short of a length and Clarke defends
much the same again, Clarke defends it to the leg side
defended by Haddin
defended safely
driven down past the bowler
Clarke leans out of his crease and pushes away to off
fullish on leg and Clarke gets some handy runs in the dying stages of the day, he's driven this one all the way along the ground through mid-on for a boundary
and the last ball of the day is pushed away to off
full just outside off and Haddin is underway immediately with a firm push in front of point
full on a tighter off stump line and Haddin punches firmly back to Broad
length ball two feet wide of off stump, left alone
length again, off stump line, blocked in the crease
short ball pulled but mistimed to midwicket on the bounce
full ball angled in and Haddin is hurried into blocking with only a half-stride forward
first ball Clarke is down the wicket, he tries to go over the top and spoons it over cover off a huge outside edge, that is remarkably fortunate and brings him fifty
down he comes again and works wide of mid-off for a quick single
length ball on off stump blocked on the front foot
too short cut but Haddin only gets a bottom edge into the turf that Prior fields
nice flight onto middle and leg, Haddin defends forward
back to force to cover point from just outside off
full ball at the stumps, squirted off a thick inside edge in front of long leg and good running brings two
good length at the stumps, Clarke forward and blocking up the wicket
touch fuller but Clarke was content to play from the crease and almost got one snuck past him, kept it out well enough back to Broad
angled in and strikes Clarke on the pad that will be sliding down leg, so not out given to the loud lbw appeal from Broad
bumper, a touch too wide of off stump so Clarke gets inside it easily enough
full delivery at the stumps, a touch straight and Clarke is able to tuck this wide of mid-on for a single
length ball on the stumps, Clarke forward watching it carefully and defends in front of short leg
down the track and chips this over mid-on, good connection and a couple of bounces brings four, much better than his first effort
a step down and just blocking around off stump
forward and defended in front of the off stick
skipping down again and just patting it back to Panesar
again taking a walk up the wicket, clips against the turn and finds mid-on
length on the off stump, Clarke stays in the crease and dabs towards the leg side
length delivery a foot and a half wide of off stump, left alone
short ball, Haddin stays inside the line and allows it to pass through to Prior
back of a length on off stump, blocked in the crease
short ball at the body, pulled and it comes off the glove I think and away from Prior, not overly in control
full at the off stump, kept out with minimal foot movement
tossed up and Clarke advances, meets it on the full and clips through midwicket, deep square leg comes around and rather lazily Swann slides with his foot on the rope as he flicks it back
flatter trajectory and just blocked up the wicket
floaty wide delivery, left well alone outside off
just back in length and Clarke is back in a flash to cut for four in front of point, excellent footwork again
shimmying down again, this time clips wide of mid-on and steals a run
blocked in the crease around the stumps
back of a length just outside off stump, punched to cover
back foot punch to mid-off this time
a bit of width and Clarke flashes a back cut for four, this is dangerous stuff from the Aussie skipper, 300 up in quick time, the hosts with the momentum
fourth stump line, Clarke blocks in the crease
full delivery just outside off, Clarke forward to block
straighter line, fuller length, Clarke clips to mid-on
tossed up on the stumps and Haddin stands and delivers a lofted drive straight over the bowler's head, Panesar sends back a scout
back on his stumps and dabs behind Carberry for just a single, fifty stand comes up in 77 balls, threatening
down the wicket and drives to short extra cover, wasn't quite to the pitch there
a step out but a forward defence into the covers here

Clarke waits for the turn and dabs off the front foot behind Carberry, calls Haddin through for a quick single and the throw was poor and Haddin gets back, had the thrown been more accurate Haddin would have been out, Carberry was off balance and couldn't get any power behind the throw, another missed chance
length ball blocked around off stump in the crease
little extra bounce from just outside off, Clarke a touch surprised in blocking just outside his off stump
fuller delivery on a similar line, blocked into the covers
length ball on off, defended firmly up on the off side
fuller ball, nicely driven but can't evade mid-off
straighter line on a length, tucked into midwicket
more runs, Clarke opens the face on a ball two feet outside off and guides it behind point
a little turn from around the wicket, Haddin adjusts in the crease and nudges it past short leg
a cut stroke from a ball not all that short, it comes off a bit of a top edge but lands well short of point
steps down the wicket and clips effortlessly to long on
off stump line, Haddin keeps it out from the crease
forward on the stumps and runs this off the inner half of the bat past short leg for a single
too straight and this is easily tucked behind square on the leg side
forward to a length ball that just shaped in a touch, Clarke able to work with the angle down to long leg
blocked on the back foot just outside off stump
back foot press this time, it doesn't come on as Haddin hoped and he finds Anderson
much fuller at the stumps, Haddin forward to keep it out up towards mid-on
forward and pushed wide of Pietersen at mid-off for an easy single
just back in length around off stump, Clarke stands up and defends easily
poor line outside leg stump, easily clipped out to deep midwicket
tossed up around middle and leg, blocked coming forward
down the wicket and clipped along the floor to short midwicket
a forward press and then back on his stumps, nudging with the angle past leg slip
floated up on middle and off, a firm punch down to long on
down the track and a clip to deep square leg with the angle
a little shape in, played forward up towards mid-on
forward again, this time out outside off, pushes to cover
full on the stumps, driven a touch loosely to mid-off
bumper, easily ducked beneath
length ball two feet outside off, Clarke guides it away to third man, Carberry has a decent distance to travel and they can get back for the second
oh lovely, shot of the morning, flourishing cover drive, not much wrong with the delivery, just full of a length on off stump and Clarke flashes the blade through it and timed it to perfection
tossed up on the stumps, slog swept hard, there's a man out at deep midwicket but can only turn and watch it land in the seats
swept again, not with the same power and reaches deep square leg
flat ball on leg stump, blocked forward in front of short leg
forward just outside off to block up on the off side
down the track and clipping through square leg, Clarke gets off 87
length ball on off stump, blocked up the wicket
touch straighter and worked out to deep square leg
pulled, a complete miscue, Panesar comes in from long leg but he can't get there in time and Haddin gets away with it
full ball on off stump, Clarke forward to push up the wicket
slightly wide of off stump and guided down to third man
full ball at the stumps, pushed up to mid-on
Clarke defends from the leg-stump line
Clarke winds up for a big sweep, but it's a pretty safe one, along the ground behind square

Swann has a shout for lbw here, he is reasonably confident but the three-man conference ends when Cook walks away, making his view clear. It was given not out, and no review eventuates. Looked to be turning down leg
Haddin goes for the sweep now, toe-edges it and the short boundary means that has lobbed for six! He didn't get that anywhere near off the middle, but the boundary is short
worked behind square for a single

action aplenty here as Clarke gets an inside edge that flies to the man at very short leg, and it's a sharp chance that's been dropped, and then as Clarke had danced down the pitch there was almost a half run-out opportunity too, but the quick flick to Prior didn't end up with the bails coming off. Clarke survives - very tough catch chance though for Bell under the helmet
drives to cover
on the back foot, Haddin punches to the off side
some width outside off now and Haddin goes back to punch that through cover point, well timed and that boundary takes Australia past 350
defended from off stump
another boundary as Stokes again gives Haddin too much width, a bouncer gone wrong, perhaps, and all Haddin had to do was steer that to third man for four
goes back into his crease to push to off
Swann still around the wicket, this time Clarke doesn't play and takes on on the pad - he doesn't want to give Bell another chance in close
a touch straighter from Swann, Clarke goes right back towards his stumps to defend
a big stretch forward from Clarke to defend, he gets hit on the pad and Swann optimistically asks for lbw, Dharmasena isn't interested - hit him just outside the line of off and a long way forward
pushed down to mid-on
turning down leg again from Swann, Haddin just steers it behind square for an easy run. That's the 100 partnership, what a great effort from the captain and his deputy, just when Australia needed it
Clarke this time works a run through square leg - easy runs there
better line and length from Stokes, but Clarke has no problem angling the bat and steering it along the ground to third man - easy with no slips in place
beaten outside off! Wow, that was unexpected - Stokes banged it in short of a length and perhaps it just nipped away a touch, Clarke tried another dab but that fizzed past the outside edge
Clarke rocks onto the back foot to punch a single through point, he's up to 96 now
Haddin flashes at one outside off, misses, and Prior seems vaguely interested in a caught-behind appeal but there was no edge according to Real-Time Snicko
fullish length and swinging in a touch, Haddin's drive can't beat cover
good line and Haddin's steer this time can't find the gap, gully cuts it off
Clarke dances down the pitch and is this the hundred? No! His drive is straight, but Broad does wonderfully well to run across and cut it off with a dive from mid-off
Haddin clips uppishly through midwicket
closes the face and works this to square leg
advances again and he's getting there in singles for the time being, this time with a safe drive along the ground to long-on
on the back foot, Haddin clips to midwicket
some good turn there for Swann, but it's so leg-sidey that Haddin's tickle sails safely down to fine leg, and that's his half-century
defended away to the off side
solidly defended to cover by Haddin
attacking the off stump is Stokes, defending is Haddin

Stokes has struck - that's his first Test wicket! Or is it? Oh dear, it's a no-ball! It was a lovely length, drawing Haddin forward to edge behind and it was a clear edge - but Marais Erasmus asks to check the front-foot no-ball and it is a few centimetres over. Clearly a no-ball, and what a disappointment for Stokes.
angling in and struck on the pads, but that was too high
Haddin defends watchfully - can he make use of that life?
and again Stokes angles it in to off stump, again Haddin defends
clipped away to leg
Clarke uses the feet nicely here but his flick can't beat midwicket
another easy single along the ground down to long-on, Clarke momentarily considers a second to Panesar the fielder, but decides against it
turning down leg, Haddin rocks back to take it on the thigh without offering a shot
solid in defence from Haddin
Haddin defends once more
Clarke is on 99 and can't get to the hundred this ball, he defends solidly to off
this one nips in off the seam and there's good bounce, Clarke's steer finds gully on the bounce
there it is! Clarke has his second consecutive century, and he gets there with a clip off his pads through square leg for a couple of runs, raises his bat and looks relieved
banged in short of a length and Clarke works it to midwicket
swinging down leg and a stifled lbw shout from Stokes, but clearly missing
driven towards mid-off, but not timed
defended down the pitch
advances down the pitch but doesn't get it away
turns sharply from outside leg but too short - Clarke cuts to point
takes this one on the pad safely with Panesar over the wicket
again just thrusts the pad out to this one
advances down the pitch and drives to Panesar
too short, and Clarke takes advantage by going back to cut hard forward of point, nice shot
defended safely by Haddin
swinging down leg and that makes contact with nothing
clips this off the pads and it's just a single to deep backward square
Stokes nips this one back in a little, it's solidly defended to cover
a trifle short from Stokes and Clarke rocks back to pull, but doesn't quite time this one
another miscued pull, this time off the edge into the body
that's a lovely shot from Haddin, he steps down and across further to leg and lofts Panesar over midwicket, clean striking and that bounces over the boundary
turning in from over the wicket and Haddin just thrusts the pad at this
again way outside leg, Haddin tries to pad it away but it doesn't turn enough, beats Haddin and Prior and results in byes
pads it away again, Panesar might have to make them play a bit more here
again, Clarke advances and pads it away
bat and pad together to defend this time, it lobs off the pad into the off side
on the pads and Haddin clips to leg
Swann is still around the wicket by the way - Haddin works it to leg again
on the pads once more, Haddin pushes to midwicket

straighter now - this is the one that might just about get the batsman in trouble as Haddin plays back and is struck on the pad. Erasmus says not out lbw, England think about a review but decide against it.
working it to short leg on the bounce
a touch quicker and straighter and it is defended
Clarke advances to Panesar and pads this one away to the off side
goes back and uses the bat this time, defends from middle and leg
tossed up outside leg, Clarke leans forward to defend
on the legs, padded away
on leg stump and turning, Clarke defends
down leg and this one beats the pad, Prior stops it from running away for byes
flighted on middle stump and it's fullish, Haddin's push back down the pitch is stopped by Swann
turning again down leg, Haddin clips to square leg
nice use of the feet this time as Haddin gets to the pitch and drives along the ground down to long-on
Clarke nimbly moves down the pitch and covers the spin, clipping to midwicket
much the same again, but this one does just beat midwicket
tossed up on leg stump, Haddin defends
over the wicket to leg stump where Clarke defends coming forward and playing with the turn to the off side
rocks back to this and cuts away to the man in the deep
touch short and Haddin is cutting this time, finds cover
floated up and driven pleasantly down to long off
down the track and swung out to deep square leg having not got to the pitch of the ball
forward on the stumps and rolled back up the wicket
length ball just outside off, Clarke stays leg side of it and guides down to third man
just back of a length and defended simply to leg
fuller length and Haddin is hurried into keeping this out on the crease
slightly shorter again, back and across, Haddin plays to midwicket
fuller again, some shape in and Haddin is forward in defence
length delivery around off stump, knocked up on the off side
touch short and cut hard to deep point
floated up nicely onto off stump, Haddin forward and gets a thick outside edge towards point
waits for this slightly wider ball to come on before chopping it to Carberry at backward point
floated up again on the stumps, Haddin blocking up the wicket this time
defends from the crease here, dabbing it towards silly point
forward again playing up to extra cover
length delivery, definitely a hint of in-ducking reverse swing, Clarke keeps it out on the crease
another length ball that tails into the off stump where Clarke meets it with a full blade
stump to stump, another block
touch wider line and Clarke drives on the up to cover
once more towards middle and off, Clarke blocking in the crease
forward again pushing up to mid-off, a rare maiden
Haddin back on the off stump and pushing on the bounce to silly point
back again and blocking a straighter ball
forward here, running a floated delivery back to the bowler
wider on the crease, angled into the stumps, another front foot block
after Haddin had firstly pulled away, he goes back and cuts to cover
off stump delivery blocked in the crease, another maiden
first runs for a while as Anderson strays onto the pads and gets clipped down to long leg
length delivery a foot outside off and pressed out to the off side sweeper
forward blocking just outside off back to Anderson
tight line and another block
full on middle and leg, clipped out to deep square leg
full on the stumps and Clarke swings through the line, times it perfectly back past the bowler and brings the 400 up
floated up onto middle and leg, blocked coming half-forward
back and across playing back up to Panesar
touch short, cut firmly to cover
Haddin on his stumps, defending
just creates a bit of room for himself and drives a slightly overpitched delivery down to long off
step down and just blocked up the wicket
back of a length on off stump, defended very comfortably
fuller but the line was too straight and Clarke easily clips out to deep square leg
very full on the off stump, Clarke forces it up to mid-on

full length two feet wide of off stump and Clarke chases after it going up and over mid-off, it was a slower ball from Broad and it's nearly worked but Clarke has enough on this to evade Pietersen and get it to the rope to bring up the 150 partnership
another drive, this a better stroke but can't escape mid-on
a long reach outside off stump with only a defensive stroke, should have been left, Haddin plays and misses
forward on off stump defending to silly point
fuller and driven back to the bowler
another drive back to the bowler
waits for this in the crease and drops it up on the leg side
down the ground and goes over the top, long off is back there but Clarke opens the face and steers it wide of the fielder, superb stroke
again using his feet plants a single down to long off
forward press from just outside off to cover
back of a good length, dabbed down in front of point
bumper, Clarke hooks and gets nowhere near hitting it probably, a big top edge runs fine of long leg and Clarke gets away with an error, he took that ball from a long way over his head
length ball outside off stump played from the crease into the gully
fuller and wide enough for Haddin to flash the hands at, finds deep point
full delivery angled into the off stump, Clarke blocks it coming forward
floated up on the stumps, driven down to long off
over the wicket, leg stump line, Clarke blocks in the crease
more flight here, Clarke forward and drops this into the leg side
tucks this off a length through square leg
back around the wicket, bowls on a length and Haddin blocks in the crease
a rare sweep, taken off middle and leg, plenty of bat on it and it runs away to the long leg rope
off stump length delivery, Clarke dabs it square on the off side
around the wicket, full on middle and leg, clipped firmly to mid-on
length delivery, a foot wide of off stump, left alone
angled across Clarke and he uses the line to steer a ball just back in length to third man, nice control
back over the wicket, good length on off stump is blocked
short ball outside off, pulled through square leg to the man in the deep
floated up onto leg stump, pushed carefully back to the bowler
touch shorter allowing Clarke to go back and clip through square leg
blocked around the off stump in the crease
slog swept from outside off to the shortest part of the ground, struck well, no-one out there
goes again and finds the same boundary, this one all the way, lovely strike
now drags it down outside off and gets struck through the off side, a couple wide of the deep cover
first up, Haddin tries to swing into the leg side, finds deep square leg
rocks back and cuts to cover point
a step down the wicket and drive to short cover
waits for this right back on the stumps and plays a delightful late cut that runs down towards third man, Panesar chases back
floated up just outside off and clipped down to long on
back foot punch to point
back on the stumps and played into the cover
a late cut, Carberry on the scene quickly, Clarke wanted a single, Haddin didn't, the throw comes into the bowler's end and Clarke is back in by a frame on the replay, very very close
yorker length, Haddin digs it out up towards mid-on
back foot push to cover from off stump
forward just outside off stump, dabbed towards cover
too short, cut hard but straight to cover
defended from leg stump
pushed away to midwicket

and there is the all-time Adelaide sixth-wicket record, as Clarke drives uppishly through mid-off - and I mean through - because Stuart Broad couldn't stop it, he was half expecting it to carry to him for a catch
pushed away to the leg side
clipped away through midwicket as Clarke advances down the pitch again
Haddin goes for the slog-sweep again and just gets away with it! Ben Stokes is at deep midwicket and despite a leap from the rope, he's unable to quite reach it

what is this? A wicket! Stokes this time has his first Test victim! Clarke has tried to turn this through square leg but a leading edge lobs up to midwicket where Anderson dives forward to take the catch. And relief for Stokes as his foot was safely behind the line this time!
dismissed_batsman_text: MJ Clarke c Anderson b Stokes 148 (350m 245b 17x4 0x6) SR: 60.40

commentary_text: Johnson watchfully pushes to cover
Johnson goes back in his crease to defend outside off
Stokes bangs in a short one now, but Johnson ducks comfortably under it
Johnson gets off the mark with a tuck off his hips through square leg
Haddin moves into the nineties now, with a boundary through third man - hard to say if that was quite deliberate as it was a bit edgy, but with no slips in place that was a boundary all the way
leans forward to defend
pushed away to the leg side
tossed up on off stump and Johnson drives to mid-off
some nice curve in to middle and leg, but no real turn, and Johnson defends
too flat this time and Johnson just rocks back and crunches this through cover - powerful stroke
drifting in from around the wicket, Johnson goes back to defend
Haddin on the back foot now, he defends
Stokes goes fullish on the pads, Haddin's drive can't beat mid-on
Haddin isn't worried about the nervous nineties! He has just lobbed Stokes over mid-on for a boundary, that is such a typical Brad Haddin stroke
on the back foot and crunches it to mid-off

another swing from Haddin and another boundary, though this one didn't go where he intended. It's a slash outside off and perhaps a bit closer to him than he expected, his thick edge flies through the vacant first slip region and away for four
solid in defence to finish the over
Johnson drives to the off side, can't find a gap
curving in from around the wicket and Johnson defends

and there's another wicket! Johnson has misjudged Graeme Swann's flight, driving uppishly and trying to clear mid-on but it has provided Stuart Broad with one of the simpler catches he will take. Might have been a bit of over-spin from Swann too, well bowled
dismissed_batsman_text: MG Johnson c Broad b Swann 5 (13m 13b 1x4 0x6) SR: 38.46

commentary_text: tossed up outside off and Siddle defends
Siddle dances down the pitch, nice use of the feet, he covers the spin and defends
quicker ball, trying to squeeze through the defences of Siddle, but he keeps it out
Haddin still searching for the hundred, he works the ball to midwicket but finds the fielder

there's the hundred for Brad Haddin! He's done it with a well-placed pull through midwicket to the boundary. Well played Brad Haddin, that's his fourth in Test cricket and his first in three years, the last one came at the Gabba in the last Ashes series in Australia. He was dropped early here, and caught off a no-ball, but he has certainly made England pay
defended safely this time
fuller length now and Haddin defends
Stokes looking for the yorker here, but it's a touch full and Haddin drives to mid-on
banged in at the hips of Haddin, he clips it away through square to retain the strike
some sharp turn from Swann, but Haddin doesn't have too much trouble working it behind square
Siddle uses the feet and turns this into a low full toss, but his drive can't beat mid-off
not much drift there, just turn in to off stump, and Siddle defends
uses the feet again, Siddle's in a dancing mood, and prods this to mid-on
Siddle goes for the sweep now and this one almost gets past him as he walks across the stumps - a bit of glove and this lobs over the keeper
leans out of his crease to defend once more
again Stokes looks for the yorker, but it's too full and driven to midwicket
clipped away through midwicket and the runs keep ticking over
Stokes has his second wicket, and that was a lovely delivery! He's angled this in and managed to get this ball to straighten a bit, Siddle plays straight and gets a thick edge through to the keeper
dismissed_batsman_text: PM Siddle c †Prior b Stokes 2 (11m 9b 0x4 0x6) SR: 22.22

commentary_text: not this time though, he's off the mark with a nice back-foot drive through point
driven back to the bowler
steered away to backward point
Haddin has tried to launch the big slog sweep again but this one is a bit fuller and he doesn't get hold of it, gets enough on it for a single though
Harris defends watchfully from off stump
plays back in his crease now and works it to short leg
tossed up to tempt Harris, and he is indeed tempted, lofts a drive over mid-off and gets enough timing on that to have it outrun the fielder running back
pushed away to cover point, can't find the gap
quicker ball at 99kph, almost a leg-stump yorker, but Harris picks it and flicks a single through square
Harris punches this to cover, straight to the fieldsman
powerful shot from Harris! He's a muscular man, but that also required timing, and he's pulled Stokes in the air forward of midwicket, it has positively raced to the boundary
banged in short again but it doesn't bounce as high as Harris expects, his pull misses and it lobs to the off side off his body
Harris launches a big off-drive this time as Stokes pitches full, but despite being well timed the shot has found mid-off
bouncer from Stokes, this one does get up a bit, but Harris is able to duck it
another bouncer and Harris shapes to hook this, pulls out at the last minute and it sails safely through to Matt Prior
Haddin tries another windy slog-sweep, but misses this
defended away to the leg side
Haddin waits on this and drives to long-on
Swann is around the wicket to Harris, who misses one turning down leg
Harris has cleared the boundary! He's decided Swann is there to hit, and has smashed this over midwicket and into the crowd!
he goes again and clears midwicket again! I though that was a replay! Almost identical as Harris again thumps Swann into the crowd over deep midwicket
angled in towards leg stump and Haddin gets it away off the thigh to square leg
Harris lifts this one uppishly just short of the catching man at midwicket

Broad wants lbw here, it's dipping in towards middle and leg, umpire Dharmasena turns it down but England ask for a review. Well, he has definitely hit the ball, but it's a question of whether his inside edge came just before or just after it hit the front pad. It looks almost simultaneous. Hot Spot doesn't shed much light on which was first. The umpire's call was not out, and there's not enough evidence to suggest that was a clear wrong call, so England lose their review.
on the back foot now, Harris punches to cover
driven to mid-off, can't find the gap
clipped through square leg
full toss to begin and it's driven down towards long-on
driven to mid-off
pushed back down the pitch
Harris rocks on to the back foot and crunches this through cover, he's enjoying the licence to have a whack here
Panesar drops the length on this one and it turns enough to catch the edge, but flies safely wide of slip
leans forward to defend
length ball on the stumps, clipped through square leg
angled in and strikes the pad as Harris looks to clip to leg
length just outside off, Harris pushing towards point
yes then no no no as Harris eventually decides against a sharp single into the covers following a dab from outside off
played from the crease in the direction of backward point
fuller and a chance to drive, finds cover
over the wicket, floated up outside leg stump, kicked away
kicked away again, it passes past the leg stump
slog swept into the deep, lands a few yards in front of Carberry at deep square leg
thought of a charge then adjusted and cut out to deep cover
gives himself room and cuts with the angle wide of the cover sweeper
slog swept over square leg, firmly struck for his fifth six
good length on off stump, a firm punch back up the wicket
bumper, easily ducked
length on the stumps, tucked back up towards the bowler
much fuller on off stump, firmly punched to mid off
just back of a length and pulled out to deep square leg

slashes at a wide one and nicks behind and England have finally removed Australia's wicketkeeper. Quite a lazy cut stroke at a wide delivery without moving his feet and it took a thick top edge that carried low through to Prior who took the catch smartly
dismissed_batsman_text: BJ Haddin c †Prior b Broad 118 (274m 177b 11x4 5x6) SR: 66.66

commentary_text: full just outside off, driven firmly to point
floated up outside off, a big swing takes a thick outside edge that evades cover
back and cut firmly to cover
steps away to leg and cuts hard wide of deep cover, can they get back for two? No
defensive push up the wicket off the back foot
same again to a straight ball
fuller this time and knocked back to Panesar again
firmly punched into the covers
played from the crease again, knocked from off stump to cover
a mow across the line from just back of a length brings four through midwicket, a touch agricultural
length ball on off stump, dropped into midwicket and there's an easy single because two men are back on the leg side fence
full delivery tails into off stump, driven without timing to mid-on
wide on the crease, angled in and strikes the pad low down, huge cry for lbw, not out given and England are out of reviews, probably going down leg
gives himself room and cut out to the man in the deep
blocked on the stumps from the crease
swept off middle stump and nails it behind square and beats the man in the deep
goes for another and misses but this is outside the line of off stump
played from the crease just outside off to mid-off
tossed up on middle and leg, driven to mid-on
back foot drive from just outside off out to the deep point
full, angled in towards the pads, Lyon just keeps it out to midwicket
length ball on the stumps and the former groundsman blocks it
length ball a foot outside off is well left alone
off stump on a length, dead-batted in the crease
full and driven off the stumps to mid-on
tucked off the stumps through midwicket, wide of the deep fielder and they get back for a second
watched carefully as he came down the pitch and knocks it down to long on
just back of a length, clipped past short leg for a single
clears the front leg and whacks it over the leg side, nails it once more and picks out the gap between deep square leg and deep midwicket
forward on off stump and pressed up to mid-off
down the wicket and tries to play down the ground, gets an edge into his boot
length on off stump, blocked in the crease
plays inside the line to a back of a length ball outside off
fuller and straighter, Lyon plays a forward defence up the wicket
left outside off but it wasn't very far away, died on Prior too
too straight and tickled down the leg side
full delivery on the stumps, blocked coming forward
length outside off stump, Lyon forces it off the back foot and gets a flashing edge that whistles past Anderson at slip and runs away towards third man
steps away to leg and cuts through the off side, finding the gap, fifty for Harris what a fine innings, some way to bounce back from a king pair in this match three years ago
now a delicate paddle sweep brings runs backward of square on the leg side
very full, Lyon tried to swing it down the ground but only dug it out to Swann's right
but connects with this heave-ho, a slog sweep sails over midwicket
Lyon sweeping now and two more for him backward of deep square leg and Australia have declared.
full and a little bit of away swing, Cook leaves it easily
slightly tighter line and left again
what on earth is this from Cook, he has a disgusting stab at a back of a length ball outside off, awful stroke with no foot movement, mercifully form him he missed it
fuller on off stump, Cook only half forward and blocking off the inner half of the bat
length on the pads, off the thigh guard and it runs behind square leg for a quick leg bye
95mph bumper, Carberry plays it well, ducking well beneath it
leg stump full toss and put away nicely through square leg, England let out a sigh of relief
length just outside off, Cook blocks up on the off side
little too full and pleasantly driven from just outside off past mid-off, won't run all the way for four
full length on a fourth-stump line, well left
again full, tighter line and blocked back to the bowler
wide enough to allow Carberry to shoulder arms again
able to leave again, just a little wide
just back of a length, two feet wide of off stump, left alone
full on the stumps and Cook nearly chips it to leg but manages to keep it down in front of midwicket
again Cook has a dabble outside off, might have withdrawn the bat in time here but it was certainly indecisive, sort of trying to cut wide of off stump

cleaned him up! Johnson on the charge again, beaten Cook for pace past the outside edge and Cook was nowhere near it. It might have straightened a fraction from an off stump line but Cook has simply been done for sheer pace at over 90mph, didn't get forward enough, tried in vain to get the bat down on it but seem to be aiming at mid-on and missed it completely
dismissed_batsman_text: AN Cook  b Johnson 3 (13m 11b 0x4 0x6) SR: 27.27

commentary_text: full on leg stump, clipped to mid-on
full and wide enough of off stump to leave alone
plays inside the line to a back of a length ball sliding across him
dabs a ball of tighter line down into the covers playing from the crease
tighter line again and Carberry able to move this from the crease to midwicket
fuller length but left alone outside off
forward to a ball on off stump and blocked into the covers
too wide and easily left outside off
bumper that goes over off stump as Root ducks comfortably
