length ball on off stump and Root calmly knocks it back up the pitch
goes to force off the back foot and plays and misses, not a good idea that stroke to a ball angled across him
back on his stumps and gets a thick inside edge out to long leg
bumper down the leg side, ignored
fuller but left outside off this time
back of a length on off stump, Root dabs it down towards point
nicely bowled, brings Root forward just outside off and it nibbles away to beat him, that's where it has to be with the new ball
touch wider and Root shoulders arms
length ball that Root waits for in the crease and angles into gully from off stump
defended around a similar area from the crease
back of a length on off stump and patted into the off side
on the off stump, Carberry defends
wow, that was fast! A 152kph bouncer, accurate too, and Carberry did very well to duck under that. Serious pace, that
probing on off stump now and Carberry is happier with that, defends
Johnson is around the wicket now, and slams down another short one at 152.5kph, Carberry ducks it
fuller length now and Carberry flicks it away to deep backward square
back over the wicket to Root and the ball keeps a touch low, Root defends
drifting down leg and Carberry goes the sweep but can't find the gap
oh, good ball, drifts in and pitches in line, turns enough to beat the bat and hits Carberry on the leg, a strong appeal from Australia is turned down and they don't ask for a review
Carberry is watchful, he defends
edgily defended by Carberry
Lyon stays around the wicket to the right-handed Root, who clips it away behind square
flighted in towards middle and off, not much turn this time, and Carberry blocks it
begins at 133kph outside off, and Root shoulders arms
fuller and straighter, Root drives to mid-on
Siddle bangs it in short of a length, Root leaves it go through to Haddin
a little bit of inswing towards middle and leg, Root defends with a straight bat
right line, right length and Siddle beats Root outside off
solidly defended towards the leg side
a touch short from Lyon, and Carberry rocks back to cut hard but can't beat point
uses the feet this time to come down the pitch and defend
lovely drift from Lyon, Carberry leaves one that pitches outside off and turns a touch further away
flighted again, Carberry nudges away to point
beaten outside off now as this one really grips on the pitch and turns - two slips in here and Australia are building the pressure on Carberry
oh, beaten again! Beautiful bowling from Lyon, this one was straighter and forced Carberry to play, turned just enough to beat the outside edge
just outside off and it's defended by Root
angling in to the pads now and Root drives along the ground, the straighter of the two short midwickets collects
left alone outside off - and only just outside - as this one moves in with the angle and doesn't miss off peg by a great deal
goes wide of the crease now and angles it in to middle stump, Root defends
again Root can't find a gap, pushes to cover
Root goes back in his crease to defend again, the runs just are not coming for England
there's some release for Carberry, gets one that is short enough to cut and places it forward of point to pick up a much-needed boundary
nudges towards the off side
Carberry goes right back in his crease to defend now
leans out now to defend once more
nice whippy stroke from Carberry, he's picked the length here and gone back to pull a slightly shorter ball through the gap, and it's not a big one, at midwicket - good placement
big turn from Lyon, but actually too much to really worry Carberry
Siddle continues to probe just outside off, Root defends with bat and pad close together
Root goes back to defend again, wants to find a single but can't
comes wider of the crease to angle it onto the pads and Root uses that angle to clip it through square leg, and good running to pick up two
edgy from Root as he pokes outside off, a thick edge bounces short of Clarke at second slip and gets away through his hands
pushed out to the off side safely
on the back foot, Root steers it down into the ground towards point
Lyon drifts it in again and Carberry defends with a straight bat
Carberry comes forward then goes back, picking the length and punching behind point
turn outside off, Carberry leaves it alone
again Lyon pitches it just outside off, turns it away, and again Carberry leaves
leaves it alone yet again, good turn from Lyon but not making Carberry play just at the moment
a fraction straighter and this time Carberry plays, but his cut is well cut off at point
beaten outside off at 139kph - Root pushes at it and that was not far away from the edge
driven off the pads along the ground to the squarer of the two short midwickets
squeezes a thickish inside edge away behind square leg, can't turn this one into two
'wait there' is the call as Carberry pushes to point, the fielder comes around to collect
Siddle angles it across Carberry, who leaves it alone
left alone outside off
shortish and Root pulls to deep square leg
left alone outside off, it's gripping and turning though
Carberry goes for the sweep and gets this one through the field, nicely placed
defended from on the stumps
turning away from the left-hander, who leaves it
Johnson starts at 142.9kph, Root goes back onto his stumps to defend
banged in short of a length and Root pushes to point off the back foot
Root jumps back into the crease and defends with a straight bat
fuller now from Johnson and Root again defends on the back foot
full again and just outside off at 145kph, Root drives towards cover
Root defends once more to the off side
probing just on off stump, Carberry defends
angled in to Carberry, who clips to leg
Carberry goes back into his crease and defends, watchful stuff here from the England top order, they just want to get to stumps without any further problems
shouts of 'caaatch' as Carberry gets a thickish inside edge off the flap of his pad and it's lobbed up on the leg side, but short of square leg
left alone outside off
straight-bat defence once more from Michael Carberry
Johnson tests Root outside off and it's defended safely
angled it towards off and Root squeezes it away to square leg
defended safely to the leg side
Johnson probes outside off at 147kph, Root calmly defends and shouts 'no!', he's looking reasonably solid here

ouch! Root takes one on the body at 148kph! Banged in short and whether Root lost sight of the ball or just got out of position or what, he just took it right on the chest. Absolutely thudded into what you'd presume must be some heavy padding
and Johnson follows up with the probe outside off, which Root prods at and misses
swinging in from around the wicket and Carberry defends
Harris digs in a bouncer but it's wide of off, easily evaded by Carberry
Carberry goes back in his crease to defend once more, he's got his eyes on stumps
closes the face and works this to leg
beaten outside off now, Harris angles it in and Carberry's straight bat is inside the line
solid in defence once more as Carberry nudges to off
angles in from around the wicket, Root defends
banged in shorter of a length at 145kph and Root defends off the back foot
short of a length once more and Root defends - it's a no-ball
fuller and straighter, Root watches carefully and just defends it straight back down the pitch
just a touch too wide of off to tempt Root, he left it alone

oh, run-out chance?! What are England doing here? Joe Root has nearly sold Carberry down the river from the second-last ball of the day! It's a back-foot push to cover and Root takes off for the single, the throw from Chris Rogers is wide of the stumps but had it hit Carberry was well short!

Carberry survives the last ball, hit on the pads but Australia decide against using a review as that looked to be sliding down leg. Ah, but what have we here? Replays show that in fact was hitting leg! That would have been overturned had Australia asked for a review, Carberry was very fortunate that Australia didn't review that.
length ball two feet wide of off stump, left alone
tighter line, a touch shorter, dabbed down into the gully
fuller and wide again, left easily
driveable length, flowing stroke to mid-off
more of a good length on the off stump, blocked up on the off side
slightly shorter length, defended in the crease around off stump
just a loosener, 87mph, blocked in front of off stump
full on leg stump, struck firmly and well saved at square leg
similar line and Carberry gets into a bit of tangle blocking it off inside edge and pad on the front foot
first bumper of the day, 92mph too, Carberry well under it
forward on off stump to block up the wicket
length on off stump, tucked up on the off side and a second maiden
good length on off stump, Root blocks in the crease
fuller and nicely driven back to the bowler from off stump
good length and Root slightly caught on the crease, gets an inside edge behind square on the leg side and a quick single opens the day's runscoring
around the wicket, full length a foot wide of off stump, left alone
tighter line and Carberry plays from under his nose towards cover point
touch wider again and Carberry able to leave once more
back of a length on the stumps, Root dabs it down in front of short leg
bumper just down the leg side, Root stays inside it
better bumper, right on target and Root has to dart under it, well played
full length a foot outside off, Root only half-forward to drop it into the covers
full again, well wide of off stump and left alone
length on off stump, Root plays from the crease again and dabs towards point
just back of a length, Carberry plays with soft hands around the off stump and runs it down through the vacant third slip area for a couple
angled down the leg side, Carberry had a flick at it and there was a noise, it did carry to Haddin who spilled it with one hand but I'm sure that's thigh pad only
back on off stump and blocked up the wicket
wide on the crease angled to middle and off, Carberry tucks with the angle to short leg
full length on the stumps, Carberry whips hard but only finds mid-on
too straight from Harris and he gets tucked through square leg for a couple
length on off stump, Root defends back in his crease
wider line, Root punches off the back foot but only as far as cover
around the wicket which heightens the slingy effect, back of a length on the stumps, blocked
fuller length, straight line, Root defending in the crease again
85mph, Root with a chance to flick to leg but only finds midwicket
back up to 94mph, full a foot outside off, Root was slow coming forward to it but ran it into the covers
around the wicket, tossed onto the stumps, Carberry forward to block
swept firmly off the stumps, a bit of a top edge, no-one back at deep midwicket so it's a calculated risk, man at deep square leg runs around to field
forward playing in front - only just actually - of silly point, softer hands needed
forward and dropping this down more comfortably in front of Bailey at silly point
back and this turns a little and bounces, Carberry tries to drag the bat inside the line but I fancy he was beaten there back on off stump
carefully forward to this and blocking up the wicket
full and wide, pleasantly driven for four through the covers, worst ball of the morning and Root put it away
length delivery on off stump, Root drops it in front of point and sets off for a comfortable single, unlike last night Carberry responded quickly enough
full on leg stump, another poor ball, and Carberry brings the fifty up with a flick wide of long leg
nicely back on it is Johnson, decent length just outside off, Carberry plays and misses where he should have left it alone
fuller and played in front of backward point, Carberry this time calls Root through for a sharp run and they get home easily
weak short ball way down leg
floated up on the stumps by 'Lyno', Carberry plays it back to him
fuller and nudged up to cover from just outside off
fuller again and Carberry can drive this time, forced out to cover point
now uses his feet and plays a delightful drive through cover, excellent batting, right to the pitch, weight into the shot and opened the face to get it into the gap
played from the crease, gets it off the outer half of the bat backward of point

top-edged sweep and find deep square leg can you believe it? All the hard work from Root and he's fallen to a very weak dismissal, that is a cheap surrender and Australia have been gifted the opening breakthrough, what a waste for England. Root was sweeping from well outside off, he was swinging hard and looked like he was going for slog sweep but a bit of bounce - that Lyon often gets - is his downfall
dismissed_batsman_text: JE Root c Rogers b Lyon 15 (114m 80b 1x4 0x6) SR: 18.75

commentary_text: around the wicket, full length, wide enough of off stump to leave alone
full again, a touch wider here so more easily left
tighter line here and Carberry drops it into cover and calls for a quick single that Pietersen was alive too
length a foot and a half outside off, left alone
long stride just outside off, Pietersen plays in front of gully
left again outside off
forward just outside off and knocked up the wicket
straighter line, Carberry watches it carefully and blocks into the off side
more flight and played from off stump to mid-off
tight off stump line, blocked back to the bowler
more air, driven off the boot of silly point to cover point
forward and defending up the wicket again
blocked on a length around off stump
full and two feet wide of off stump, shouldered arms

Pietersen fiddles at this outside off, Haddin takes it low and appeals immediately, nothing from anyone else but Clarke reviews looking for a faint one. Good chance for the new DRS here, there's nothing on Hot Spot to suggest an edge. Real Time Snicko doesn't have anything either so this will stay not out. Strange review that really with only Haddin interested
length ball steered away through the slips cordon and Pietersen is away
length delivery just outside off, left well alone
full length and driven off a thick inside edge in front of square leg for a couple more
touch short and pushed firmly to mid-off
few inches outside off, left alone
back to cut and gets it through cover, just a touch short and Carberry punishes it
touch short and again played off the back foot, not wide enough of mid-off for a single
forward on off stump and dabbled up the wicket
more air to off stump and blocked up the wicket again
length delivery a good distance outside off, left easily alone
oh nicely bowled, this nips back and beats Pietersen on the inside edge, where did that come from? Jagged back and went over off stump

Pietersen takes a little step down the pitch and clips straight to short midwicket and again Pietersen falls right into the trap. George Bailey juggled the chance but held on well and that is the second very weak dismissal this morning. Very very poor indeed from such a great player, flicking right into the trap and now England are in trouble
dismissed_batsman_text: KP Pietersen c Bailey b Siddle 4 (19m 12b 0x4 0x6) SR: 33.33

commentary_text: drives hard straight back to Siddle, who picks it up sharply
good line on off stump from Siddle and Bell defends carefully with a straight bat
Bell gets off the mark with an edgy sort of a drive just forward of the short catching cover, uppishly struck as well, which had the Australians interested, but safe enough
cuts hard to point and picks up a single
confident off-drive now from Bell
plenty of flight from Lyon, and plenty of foot use from Bell, who advances and drives hard to mid-off
turning in towards off stump and Bell defends
wonderful shot from Bell! You wouldn't know that he's new at the wicket from this, uses his feet to advance and lofts Lyon cleanly over long-off, beautiful stroke
solidly defended now
Siddle comes around the wicket to Carberry, who defends
Siddle probes outside off but Carberry watches it carefully and shoulders arms
good placement from Carberry, moves forward to drive through cover and although it is chased down inside the boundary, he picks up three and moves ever closer to a maiden Test half-century
Bell is full of confidence against Siddle as well as Lyon, rocks back and pulls hard and high forward of midwicket, a little top-edgy perhaps but safe enough
straight from Siddle, straight bat from Bell
strays onto the pads now and Bell clips this nicely square of midwicket and that has run away to the boundary
solidly defended by Bell now
Carberry leans forward to defend
lovely drift in from around the wicket, this grips and turns and beats the bat
cracking cut now from Carberry as Lyon drops just a tiny bit short, and Carberry picks up the length and rocks back in his crease to force that forward of point
driven towards mid-off and he can't find the gap
Carberry cuts this one as well, a little uppishly, but safely to deep point and that is Carberry's half-century, his first in Tests, well played given the wickets that have fallen around him
magnificent from Bell. What more can you say? He advances, hits with the spin of Lyon and lofts this over long-on for another six. That is a batsman full of confidence and in full control
Siddle is still around the wicket, angling it in but not making Carberry play
this time it's straighter and Carberry defends
shoulders arms once more outside off
Carberry picks up another boundary, albeit from a slightly edgy stroke as he drives hard outside off and this one flies away between point and gully, along the ground though
this one is on the hips and Carberry steps across his stumps to allow the ball through to Haddin
another super shot, this time a cover-drive from Carberry as Siddle probes on that length outside off, he has timed and placed this perfectly through the gap
Lyon is around the wicket now and Bell just drives a simple single down to long-on, who is back on the boundary now
Carberry is good at getting at Lyon's length, shapes to move forward and then rocks back to cut hard forward of point
turning from outside off further away, it's left alone
tossed up on off, Carberry leans forward to defend
quicker and flatter, but still turning enough to allow Carberry to leave it
straight ball now, again it's fairly quick and again Carberry declines to play outside off
probes outside off to begin, Bell defends
Bell goes the cut now but this one is too full, or perhaps just stays down a touch as it nips in, and his under-edge goes through to Haddin on the bounce
solidly defended by Bell
Bell drives confidently enough again but straight to point
lovely shot from Bell as he leans into a cover drive and places it perfectly, all the way along the ground to the boundary
wider of off and Bell goes the drive again, this one is a bit of an inside edge though and he doesn't get it away
fullish and wide of off first up, Carberry drives to cover point
Carberry leans forward and defends watchfully
angled across Carberry, who leaves it alone
Watson trundles in again and angles it across at 131kph, Carberry is not interested
straighter now and Carberry defends
left alone outside off once again
solidly defended just outside off
clipped away to short midwicket and Bailey does the fielding
angled in to Bell, who defends
Harris probes outside off, Bell goes the square drive but fails to beat point
straight-bat defence from Bell
again Bell defends solidly
around the wicket to Carberry, who defends
left alone outside off
short of a length and Carberry defends
fuller and just outside off, no swing for Watson, and Carberry pushes to cover
driven hard to mid-off and he can't beat the gap
Carberry goes back to defend and that completes another maiden for Watson
banged in short by Harris, haven't seen many bouncers this morning, and Bell sways out of the way easily
fuller now and getting Bell to drive, he finds cover
short again, left alone again
solidly defended again by Bell
Bell rocks onto the back foot now to punch forward of point but can't find the gap

ah, well bowled! Harris goes the short one again but this is straighter and Bell can't get out of the way, but he does well to force it down into the ground - mind you, he did not look entirely comfortable doing so
Watson is still around the wicket, Carberry is still happy to leave
again Carberry shoulders arms, you'd think both these batsmen are playing for lunch with ten minutes to go
Watson angles it in to off stump and Carberry defends
shorter of a length, Carberry coves off stump and shoulders arms again
left alone outside off again

wow! Out of nowhere Carberry has gone! We were one ball away from a fifth straight maiden over and Carberry gets a short one from Watson and goes for the pull, he absolutely creamed it out of the middle of the bat but Warner at forward square leg has thrust the hands down and somehow taken that in his left hand alone
dismissed_batsman_text: MA Carberry c Warner b Watson 60 (202m 144b 10x4 0x6) SR: 41.66

commentary_text: Johnson comes back for an over before lunch, and Bell defends
goes back onto the back foot now and defends again
a rarity here - a wide in Test cricket - as Johnson sprays this like the Mitch of three years ago, well wide of off
left alone outside off
left alone outside off once again
solidly defended from off stump
Bell goes for a shot shortly before lunch and gets away with it! Shorter of a length from Johnson, Bell punches hard off the back foot and it has flown over gully and away to the boundary
leans forward to defend safely
again tossed up on middle and leg, again Stokes defends
drifting down leg now and Stokes leans out to defend
defended once more
some drift in but too wide of off, and Stokes can leave it
again well wide of off but he plays this, safely to cover
length delivery on a fourth-stump line, Bell shoulders arms
touch wider, left again
fuller on a similar line, left again
tighter line and Bell forced to block up towards mid-off
shorter ball that Bell has to withdraw the hands inside from
short ball into the rib cage, Bell nicely on top of it to drop it towards square leg
tossed up on off stump, blocked up the wicket
blocked with a forward press again
similar line and length, Stokes forward playing up the wicket
touch short and a chance to get back to cut, on the bounce finds cover point
full length and driven to mid-off, Stokes wants a single and gets home easily because Harris fumbles, had it not it was a superb run-out chance
stays around the wicket, bowls outside off stump, Bell dabs this into the covers

full at the pads, huge appeal for lbw, not out given, Erasmus reckoned Stokes hit this, it rebounds to point, there's a run taken and the throws ends up going for four overthrows but Clarke reviews the lbw call. Johnson is mighty close on the no-ball but just okay. Replays suggest the delivery was pad first, Stokes hit his pad with the bat and Hawk Eye has it...crashing into middle and leg and Stokes is gone. Johnson quick and straight and once again too good for an England batsman. Nothing Stokes would have ever faced before this bowling. Like Cook, he was simply done for pace
dismissed_batsman_text: BA Stokes lbw b Johnson 1 (19m 12b 0x4 0x6) SR: 8.33

commentary_text: full at the leg stump, tucked up to midwicket
bumper and Prior didn't really have a clue, wrapped on the chest trying to fend it off to leg and knew nothing about it
another bumper, 93mph, that whistles past Prior's helmet as he just gets inside it

well four balls is all Prior has lasted because he's felt for one outside off stump and nicked it behind. Two rough shorties followed by one pitched up sliding across him, Prior played forward and followed it outside off, getting a thin edge through to Haddin who claimed the catch down low
dismissed_batsman_text: MJ Prior c †Haddin b Johnson 0 (3m 4b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

commentary_text: haha cleaned him up! What an over from Johnson. Fabulous fast bowling and that is surely one of the great Ashes overs. Fast on a length, Broad stepped across to try and flick to leg but has lost his leg stump. Remarkable stuff, a triple wicket maiden from Johnson! Again, the pace is simple too much for England
dismissed_batsman_text: SCJ Broad  b Johnson 0 (6m 1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

commentary_text: spins down the leg side and Bell leaves well alone
tossed up on leg stump, clipped into midwicket
length delivery that Bell drops in front of short leg
some turn past the inside edge that strikes the pad but going well down leg
floated up on off stump and Bell clips it down the ground to long on
Swann meets this on the full on off stump, sweeps to square leg and they take the single, meaning Swann will now face the hat-trick ball
length ball on leg stump and Swann chips is through a vacant midwicket for a hard-run three
back of a length around off stump Bell, not content to hang around, uppercuts over the slips and gets four, nice stroke
good length on a fourth-stump line, well left
slower ball at 81mph, back foot push to cover
another back foot push, this time evades cover for a single
bumper down the leg side, Swann swings at it and misses
leg stump on a length, blocked in the crease
floated up outside off, lovely cover drive but Bailey dives and saves really well
some turn as Bell tries to flick to leg and gets struck on the thigh pad
another cover drive and this time it would have needed three Baileys to stop it, beautiful flowing stroke
tries to flick back past the bowler with the turn but Lyon dives to his right and saves
driven back to the bowler again
nasty bumper at 91mph right on the money, Swann just tries to fend it off and pops up a catch to where silly point might have been
swish and a miss outside off to a ball just back in length but not wide enough to slash as Swann tried their
gets this away though, just a touch wider so Swann can free the hands a little more and gets a back foot punch away over extra cover for three
leg stump on a length, tucked into midwicket and they get a comfortable single

full and wide, Swann swings at it, gets a thick outside edge and Clarke takes a superb catch high over his right shoulder, a fine grab and Johnson has a five-for again. Swann was not going to sit around waiting for a ball to get him out, he chases a full wide one, didn't get his foot right out to meet it and nicks off. Another superb Australian catch
dismissed_batsman_text: GP Swann c Clarke b Johnson 7 (16m 7b 0x4 0x6) SR: 100.00

commentary_text: full and straight and knocks out middle stump! This is fast becoming one of the great fast bowling spells. Full, fast and furious that pierces the gap between bat and pad and takes the top of middle stump. Absolutely perfect from Johnson and he need only look at Anderson this time
dismissed_batsman_text: JM Anderson  b Johnson 0 (1m 1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

commentary_text: back of a length on off stump, blocked into the covers from the crease
fuller length on off stump, Bell forward and plays out to cover
leg stump and clipped wide of long leg but not wide enough for the second
bumper, well directed, Panesar ducks
fuller ball, gets out of the way I think and the ball rebounds to first slip, half an appeal but it was straight off the arm guard
another bumper, Panesar ducks and wears one on the arm guard I think, sounded painful
full on off stump, Bell pokes at it and very nearly finds short extra cover
similar line, slightly shorter length, blocked in the crease
full and sliding across Bell who leaves alone
bumper, right on line, Bell hooks and misses with the ball getting well above the stroke
back of a length just outside off, Bell clips off the back foot to point
sways inside the line and helps it up and over the slips cordon, nicely played, scant relief
bumper down the leg side, ignored
now around the wicket, another shortie, ducked again
length delivery on off stump, Panesar comes forward and blocks in front of short leg
short again, Panesar ducks well again
full on off stump, Panesar is forward and blocking to silly point
back over the wicket, length ball on off stump and Panesar blocks it firmly to the leg side
length ball a foot wide of off stump, punched without timing off the back foot to cover
another back foot push but this gets through the covers for a single
bumper, Panesar well under it
comes forward to this on off stump and pushes gently into the covers
another bumper and Panesar is up and down like a yoyo here
full and blocked up to mid-off

and we have a review for lbw. Harris angled it in and Bell was struck on the back thigh, in line with off stump. Dharmasena's call was not out and it's an umpire's call on the height - Bell survives and Australia have no more reviews
Bell reaches his half-century with a classy back-foot cut through point, that races away to the boundary
Bell opens up now, he's decided to have a crack while he can, clears the front foot and launches this over mid-off and it has managed to clear the fielder
boundaries galore in this over - poor ball swinging down leg and Bell just gets enough bat on it to glance it away to fine leg
defended on middle and leg now
Bell really has a swing at this, and this has cleared the rope! Wow! He has just sliced this away over cover and got so much on it that it has gone for six!
Siddle bangs it in short and Panesar ducks under it
angled across off stump and Panesar just prods a single through cover to get off the mark and off the strike
Bell pushes away to point and can't add to the score
bouncer from Siddle, Bell shapes to hook and then decides against it
on the hips now, Bell works it to fine leg and decides to hold on to the strike instead of taking the single
solidly defended from off stump now
defended to short midwicket and Panesar will be on strike next over
prodded away defensively by Monty
leans forward to defend
tossed up and Panesar edges it away to gully
leans forward to defend solidly once more
tossed up on off stump, well defended by Panesar
safely negotiated as Panesar prods to off
solidly defended by Bell
angles in to off stump and Bell blocks it away
Siddle bangs in the bouncer, Bell ducks underneath it
shouts from the Australians as Bell drives this uppishly towards short midwicket but it has bounced short
Bell defends watchfully from off stump
probing on off stump, and Bell defends
Lyon is around the wicket to Panesar, he beats the outside edge with one that just turns a fraction
watchful from Panesar as he leans out to defend
clipped away to mid-on, can't find a way to get off strike
dropped! Oh dear, thick edge from Panesar and Clarke at first slip gets his hands in the wrong position, almost had too much time I think, it's bobbed up off the hands or stomach and fallen safely
left alone outside off
pushed away towards point
solidly defended by Bell
probing outside off and Bell defends with bat and pad close together
shorter now and Bell swivels a pull to deep square leg and gives Siddle a look at Panesar

runs for England here as Panesar ducks into a bouncer! Didn't get up as much as he anticipated and it's clunked off the back of the helmet and flown over Haddin, not enough pace on it to get to the boundary though

struck again! This time I think Siddle may have got Panesar around the shoulder, that one also didn't get up as much as Panesar thought and he's taken his eyes off the ball and taken it on the right upper arm
solid defence after those short ones, nicely done Monty
Lyon is around the wicket and angles this across Bell, who leaves it
tossed up on middle and leg, no turn as Bell defends
flighted again and turning in from outside off, Bell goes back to punch to cover point
Bell goes right back in his crease and works it away behind square leg
Panesar leans forward to defend once more
again Panesar is watchful, defending safely to off
Siddle bangs it in short of a length and Bell defends
fuller and straighter, Bell drives towards mid-off
goes for the fuller yorker-length ball now, it is dug out by Bell
loud shout of 'nooo!' from Bell as he defends again
steered away towards backward point
Bell goes for the straight drive but it's collected by mid-on
tossed up outside off and Panesar has a dabble, his thick edge flies just out of the reach of second slip and he gets himself off strike
defended from off stump
prodded to the off side, Bell is watchful here
makes Bell play with a straighter one, he defends
there's the Bell we saw in the first session today against Lyon! He's advanced and lobbed it over long-on for six, confident, controlled and a good shot
tries to dance down again for another one but Lyon drags the length back and Bell has to defend
immediately Johnson gets one past the bat, it's taken on the thigh and lobs out towards the second slip
gone! Johnson gets the job done immediately! Quick, accurate and takes Panesar's off stump. A little inside edge onto the pad and then it clips back into the stumps and England are all out for 172
dismissed_batsman_text: MS Panesar  b Johnson 2 (60m 35b 0x4 0x6) SR: 5.71

commentary_text: just back of a good length, Rogers pokes at it outside off and it flies just wide of the outstretched hand of Ian Bell in the gully
this time Rogers leaves a slightly wider ball
fuller ball and a tighter line, Rogers blocks in front of off stump
fuller, a little away swing, left alone
length ball down leg side, Prior dives across and takes it nicely
full and swings away a little again, Rogers left it again
goes to cut first ball a delivery that isn't short enough for the shot and gets a bottom edge into the ground
back and across the off stump to defend up the wicket
full on leg stump, clipped out to deep square leg
fuller ball just outside off, dabbed into the covers
length on off stump, pushed towards midwicket
fuller on off stump, pushed back up the wicket
touch straight from around the wicket and tucked down to long leg

full ball that Rogers comes forward to and edges behind. Something to cheer for England, poor stroke, played on the walk and a thick edge carries through to Prior. Excellent length from Anderson, drawing the batsman forward and he felt for it when he probably could have left it
dismissed_batsman_text: CJL Rogers c †Prior b Anderson 2 (11m 10b 0x4 0x6) SR: 20.00

commentary_text: length down the leg side, flicked at and missed

full and wide, Watson leans out to it and slaps it straight to point and that is a poor stroke. What is he doing there? Has to reach so far out for it, second ball, and picked out Carberry who rather enjoyed that catch!
dismissed_batsman_text: SR Watson c Carberry b Anderson 0 (2m 2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

commentary_text: length ball a couple of feet outside off, easily left
similar delivery, a hint of away swing, left again
back of a length just outside off, nicely punched for four in front of square, but that was the stroke that he got out to in the first innings, needs to be careful
another firm back foot punch, this finds extra cover
full at the stumps, tucked to midwicket
similar line but more of a length ball, this is tucked in front of midwicket and they get a single
good length that Clarke thinks about playing to before withdrawing the bat
good length, still just wide enough of off stump to allow Clarke to leave alone
around the wicket, angled in and tucked behind square leg for a quick couple
good length on off stump, blocked in the crease up the wicket
full delivery that Warner was a little slow in coming forward to and blocking to midwicket where Stokes sends a silly throw over the head of Prior and they get an overthrow!
Anderson drifts into the pads and gets clipped firmly through square leg, excellent timing
good length wide enough to leave alone outside off stump
angled in to the pads, an aerial chip towards midwicket, Stokes dives and saves really well, the turns and very nearly runs out Warner running a single
knocked down from the crease in front of short leg
gorgeous delivery, sliding in and nibbles away beating the outside edge
length ball punched firmly to extra cover, needs to be just a little fuller than that
again just a touch short and Clarke sits on the back foot in front of off stump and punches to extra cover
better length but just wide enough to allow Clarke to leave alone
pulled off not too short a length, comfortably steered to long leg
yorker and dug out well
full again, pushed back up to the bowler
good length on off stump, Clarke forward with a solid block
blocked from the crease around off stump
short ball that Clarke miscues trying to turn to leg and gets a leading edge but Clarke's luck is in again as it lands just out of the reach of an onrushing Anderson
good length around off stump, Clarke blocks with inside edge and pad
full on the stumps, 86mph, pushed through midwicket and deep square leg comes around to field
bumper and Clarke is quickly under it
wide on the crease, short ball and pulled out to long leg
full on off stump, forward push back to the bowler
looked like a cutter, on the stumps, Warner tucks it into midwicket
bumper, well directed, Clarke able to let it past
forward on the stumps and pushed up the wicket
forward on off stump, gets a thick outside edge towards cover
step down the wicket and pushes back to the bowler
flatter trajectory, back on his stumps and blocking
step down the wicket and tries to play in-to-out but mistimes it to cover
leg stump line and Warner pushes carefully into the leg side, a misden
back of a length and pulled down to long on where Pietersen is stationed
only slightly back in length and short-arm jabbed through midwicket, deep square leg does the fielding
full on the stumps and dropped wide of midwicket for a single
pulled again and again finds Pietersen at long leg
full length, much better, wide enough to leave alone outside off
full length on the stumps, blocked up on the off side from the crease
tossed up on the stumps, flicked with the turn to midwicket who's just a little deeper than orthodox so they get a single
tossed up on the stumps, Warner meets it on the full and threads it through extra cover
forward, a little turn brings a thick outside edge and runs through where gully might have been
a step down the wicket and blocked with bat and pad together back to the bowler
flatter ball, dabbed up on the off side from off stump
more air now and a firm clip out to long on
nice stroke, firmly punched to cover off the back foot
full length on off stump, driven firmly to extra cover
yorker length just outside off, dug out to cover
good length a foot outside off, well left
a drive to a fuller ball just outside off, it's aerial for a time but landed just short of Carberry at point
full on the stumps, Clarke pats it gently back to the bowler
off stump, just short of a length, defended back in front of off stump
again just a little short, short-arm jabbed to midwicket
fuller and rolled to extra cover from just outside off
tossed up on off stump, rolled back to Swann
forward press just outside off, knocked into the covers
the arm ball, skids on a little and Warner chops to point, it nearly snuck past him
full and a little movement away from the bat as Clarke leaves well alone
bumper, well directed over middle and off, Clarke withdraws from a hook stroke
forced off the back foot, Carberry dives to his right and makes a smart save
good length a foot outside off, Clarke shoulders arms
full toss on off stump, Clarke pushes gently to mid-off
back on a decent length, Clarke leans out just outside off and pushes into the covers, third maiden on the trot
off stump line, defended up on the off side
flatter ball and flicked around the corner, Anderson chases from first slip back towards the fine leg rope and they get three
full delivery flicked with the turn from off stump through square leg
big slog sweep over midwicket, nailed it into the stands, big shot
tossed up again, forward and just ran into midwicket this time
arm ball outside off, angled to point off the back foot
firm push off the back foot and finds the gap between point and cover to get a single
full length sliding across Warner who meets it coming forward and plays to cover
not that short at all but slapped straight of midwicket, not timed overly well
back of a length and pushed from the crease to the right hand of the bowler
again just slightly short and gives the batsman chance to rock back, this is timed properly and it races through midwicket
much better length, full and Clarke blocks it back to the bowler
leans forward to defend
around the wicket and drifts it in, Warner advances to defend
plays from the crease this time, drives uppishly towards cover
curving in but no real spin, Warner nudges to point
leans forward to defend
sharp turn from the footmarks well outside off, and this beats Prior and slip for a bye
plenty of turn in to Warner from well outside off, he defends
goes back and cuts against the spin but can't beat point
a fair bit of turn for Monty, but Warner gets in the way of this
plays back and whips to mid-on
plays right back on his stumps to defend against a quicker spinner from Panesar
uses the feet now and drives down to long-on to keep the strike
plays right back in his crease and clips to leg
drifting on to the pads now, down leg side
Warner opens up and lofts this, well-controlled in the end as he's opened the face and lifted Swann over cover, bounces over the boundary
uses his feet but in doing so actually yorks himself, but is able to drive it down to long-off
dab sweep from well outside off, Clarke has just steered through the vacant leg slip area and fine leg cuts it off
goes back for a late cut now, Panesar does the fielding at deep backward point
quicker and flatter from around the wicket, Clarke defends
again flat, offering no flight, Clarke works it through square leg
well wide of off and Warner leaves it alone
turn and bounce now, Warner again watches it through to Prior
Warner uses his feet now and just drives to short cover
again Monty gives it no flight, again Warner defends
low full toss and Clarke drives wide of mid-off who gets across but not quickly enough to cut off a single
Warner is in the baggy green now with spin on from both ends, he leaves one outside off
left alone outside off
again it's turning away and again Warner offers nothing
goes the drive for a fuller ball now, deep cover and long-off converge and cut this off
well wide of off and turning further away, Warner is not interested
gone! Panesar has bowled Clarke with a lovely delivery, quicker ball from around the wicket and turning just enough to beat the outside edge, this has collected the off stump and Clarke is gone
dismissed_batsman_text: MJ Clarke  b Panesar 22 (77m 51b 2x4 0x6) SR: 43.13

commentary_text: leans forward to defend
Smith uses his feet nicely and clips this off his toes through mid-on
sharp turn, but Warner coves his off stump and defends
angled bat from Warner, he's steered this through gully for a single
flattish trajectory from Panesar, Smith punches to off
Panesar isn't flighting it much but Swann is, drifting it in from around the wicket and Warner drives to long-off
Smith leans out from his crease and defends
shorter from Swann but Smith can't find the gap, punches this straight to point
on the pads, works it to leg but not past the man in close
again Smith defends with bat and pad close together
tossed up outside off, Smith gets to the pitch of it and drives back to Swann
Warner uses the feet and doesn't get this off the middle
turning in from outside off, Warner covers his stumps and defends
Warner gets this one through the gap, he doesn't quite get to the pitch of this one but close enough and drives it through cover point all the way along the ground
defended back down the pitch
defended away to the off side
Warner goes back and plays with the spin, working this behind square leg
tossed up outside off and Warner drives, can't find the gap
Warner waits on this for a late cut but it is cut off
fuller ball and it's driven out to deep cover for a single
driven down along the ground towards long-on
Warner is forward and defends
Warner rocks back to cut but can't get it through the field
plenty of men around the bat as England try to maintain the pressure on Smith, he uses his feet and prods past short leg for a quick single
misfield  from Pietersen and that grants Warner his half-century - he has cut hard and Pietersen at point just missed what should have been a regulation stop, it has run away to the boundary
waits on this for a late dab past slip and Warner gets a couple more runs
another boundary now as Panesar drops too short and Warner quickly gets back into his crease and thumps this through cover point
turning in and Warner goes back to defend
quicker and on off stump, it's defended
on line to begin with, and Smith defends on off stump
forward and defending once again
vicious cut from Smith as Anderson drops short outside off, Smith finds the gap behind point and this fizzes away to the boundary
Smith drives hard but short cover cuts this one off

Smith has been adjudged lbw here, Anderson had it swinging back in and Smith offered no shot. My initial reaction was it may be too high. Smith has asked for a review, and replays suggest that was missing off stump, not moving back in enough. Had it been straight the height would maybe have been just okay, but it wasn't straightening enough and Erasmus has his decision overturned
defended back down the pitch
defended from just outside off
Warner advances down the pitch and drives this along the ground, classy shot against the spin through the gap between cover and mid-off
cut off the back foot between point and cover
Warner plays back and defends a quicker ball

close lbw shout! Turned down by Kumar Dharmasena and England have decided not to review this. It looked relatively tight, hit in line but was it turning too far? Well, we might have some idea if there was a replay but we haven't seen one yet...
defended back down the pitch
defended from off stump
flashes outside off and this one beats the bat
good, quick running between the wickets as Smith punches off the back foot forward of Carberry at point

Warner is struck on the leg trying to whip a pull through leg, there's interest in an lbw shout from Anderson but it's turned down, and he can't convince Cook to ask for a review. Sailing well over the top
whipped away to square leg, can't find the gap
angling towards the hips of Warner, whose flick finds square leg again
confident stuff from Smith, he's danced down the pitch and lofted Panesar back over his head, followed through and that was a safe shot
Panesar is around the wicket to Smith, who defends
leans out to defend once again
drifting onto the toes of Smith, who works it to leg but not through the gap
straight bat from Smith again
pushed away to cover point
solid in defence on off stump
carefully defended towards cover
solid in defence again as Anderson probes outside off
angling in towards middle stump, Warner plays back and defends
fuller length from Anderson, Warner drives on the bounce back to the bowler
Warner has had enough of defending for now, he's gone for a lofted on-drive and done enough to clear mid-on, but hasn't quite timed it well enough for a boundary, it slows up and is reeled in
Warner cuts but not past cover point
on the back foot now Warner punches to cover
banged in short of a length and Warner has crunched a pull forward of midwicket, in the air but safely wide of mid-on - can Warner get himself a hundred here?
on the pads and Warner tickles this away through square leg
Broad probes outside off, Smith defends
defended away safely to the off side
and Warner welcomes Stokes with a dismissive drive straight back down the ground for four! Uppishly played, but safely wide of the bowler and that sizzles away to the boundary
on the pads now and Warner clips a single through leg
driven away to cover, can't find the gap
Smith leans out to defend, gets a thick inside edge
Smith finds himself a run now with a drive into the turf and wide of mid-off
angled across and Warner defends from off stump, his thick edge flies away along the ground to gully
Broad probes outside off at 132.3kph, Smith shoulders arms
angled in towards middle and leg, Smith just steers this through the gap at midwicket and although it is chased down within the boundary, Smith and Warner are quick enough to run four
defended to leg this time
swinging in towards off, Smith drives to cover
worked away to midwicket off the pads
straight-bat defence from Smith
Warner skips a couple of steps down the pitch and lifts this down to long-on, didn't get hold of that though
pushed away to cover and can't beat the field
beaten outside off now as Panesar gets this one to turn sharply
bat and pad close together from Smith as he watchfully defends
again it is defended by Smith
tossed up and Smith comes forward to defend
punched off the back foot to cover
Stokes beats Warner outside off this time, nice delivery
swinging down leg and Warner gets some pad on this, picks up a leg bye
straight bat from Smith, who is keen to really spend some time in the middle
wide of off and Smith leaves it alone
angling in to middle and leg, Smith clips to square leg
Warner uses the feet again and drives an easy single down to long-on
Smith uses the feet now and defends
punched away off the back foot through point
plays back in the crease to defend
gets some width and Warner latches on to it, cuts hard through point and picks up another boundary
pulled away through mid-on this time for one more
beaten outside off as this one stays a touch low
on the pads, Warner works it away to leg
on the back foot now, Warner nudges to mid-off
good judgement from Warner as he pushes to mid-off and takes off quickly for a single
solid in defence is Smith
Smith leans out to defend once more
Warner plays back and works a single behind square leg
too short from Panesar, which allows Smith to rock back and punch a couple of runs forward of point
tossed up on off stump, it's defended
quicker and straighter, making Smith play, he defends off the back foot
drifting onto the pads, Smith defends once more
and Smith finishes with two more, cutting backward of point off a shorter ball
length ball around off stump, Cook leaves, a good leave
tighter line and Cook comes forward on off stump to play into the leg side
yorker length on off stump, Cook digs it out up the wicket
too straight, Cook tickles down to long leg and England are away
full length angled across Carberry who shoulders arms
around the wicket, length ball on off stump, Carberry blocks it towards point
full loosener way outside off, ignored
length delivery a foot wide of off, Cook leaves it alone

short ball, Cook hooks and gets a top edge, long leg comes in and takes a tumbling catch! Can you believe it. Harris with a fine effort running in off the boundary and claiming a low chance just above the ground diving forward. Cook decided to go the aggressive route this time but Plan B has also failed
dismissed_batsman_text: AN Cook c Harris b Johnson 1 (7m 7b 0x4 0x6) SR: 14.28

commentary_text: full and sliding across Root at 91mph, he leaves it alone
full on off stump, Root blocks from the crease up on the off side
full and wide and left alone, wicket maiden to start for Johnson
stays around the wicket, length delivery on off stump, Carberry forward blocking
nicely bowled, draws Carberry outside off stump and his forward push is beaten
wider and comfortably left alone
full just outside off, driven off an edge via the ground to gully
driven again, this time a more controlled stroke from off stump to cover
bumper, too high and Carberry easily under it
full just outside off, Root forward and dabbing up towards point
back of a length, blocked back on off stump
dabbed off the back foot into the covers, chance of a single quickly dismissed
slightly fuller, blocked in the crease up on the leg side
fuller again, this time towards off stump, Root dabs it into the covers again playing from the crease
full and wide, left alone
good length on off stump, Carberry defends
fuller ball, again towards off stump, Carberry digs it out into the covers
full ball at the stumps, Carberry goes to whip it into the leg side and was late on it, smashing it into his front pad
length ball around off stump, Carberry blocks towards midwicket
length ball angled in from wider on the crease, Carberry tucks with the angle to midwicket
yorker, well-directed, Carberry digs it out
forward on off stump to defends up on the leg side
length ball sliding across Root who shoulders arms
bumper down the leg side of no concern
length ball on middle and leg, defended solidly in the crease
full and wide of off stump, left easily alone
tighter line on a better length, blocked
length on the stumps again, blocked up the wicket
staying around the wicket, Carberry if forward blocking again on off stump
fuller and Carberry uses the angle to flick through square leg, finally off the mark
back over the wicket now, full on off stump, driven to extra cover
lovely stroke, overpitched and nicely put away from just outside off
drops his length and Carberry just blocks
wider line and left alone
good length on off stump, Root knocks it back up the wicket
slightly wider line, dabbed in front of point from the crease
fuller length, Root forward and gets a thick inside edge through midwicket and after 18 balls, Root is off the mark
length on off stump, Carberry blocks it up the wicket
similar line, just back of a good length here, dead-panned again
almost identical delivery, blocked in the crease
well wide of off stump and left alone
fuller length, firmly punched up the wicket and it evades Harris's dive and they get a couple
good length but Root hangs back and drops it up on the off side
shorter ball, Root went to tickle it around the corner but got hit on the thigh pad
fuller length and Root out to meet it, blocking to extra cover
bumper outside off, Root stays well away from it
another bumper, better directed, Root under it quickly
full length towards off stump, Carberry calmly forward blocking
fuller length, Carberry forward a little and leaving
length on the hip and tucked through square leg for a couple, Harris does well running to his right at long leg
fuller length at the stumps, Carberry comes forward and plays back up to the bowler
tucked through square leg again off the hip but this time just for a single because it runs too close too soon to Harris
forcing stroke off the back foot, line was perhaps a little too close for the attempted stroke, gets a thick inside edge to short leg
around the wicket, tossed into the footholds, it turns away and Carberry leaves
forward to a straighter line and blocked up to the bowler
more air, driven with the turn to mid-off
floated up and firmly punched from outside off, into the shins of silly point
wider line and left this time
touch short and worked in front of midwicket for a quick single
full, wide delivery left alone and it barely carries to Haddin
a little straight and worked out through the leg side for an easy couple
around the wicket, length delivery just wide enough of the off stick to allow Carberry to leave

short of a length, pulled and finds a diving Nathan Lyon at long leg. You can't make this up, outrageous. Absolutely no trouble whatsoever, this delivery isn't quick or even that short, Carberry has simply picked it up straight to long leg. It's another good catch with Lyon getting down low to his right
dismissed_batsman_text: MA Carberry c Lyon b Siddle 14 (52m 39b 2x4 0x6) SR: 35.89

commentary_text: length delivery wide of off stump, left alone
forward to a full ball on off stump, dropped into the covers and the fielder comes in quickly to save the single
played with the turn and tickled out to deep-backward square
around the wicket, Pietersen takes a step down and flicks behind square to get off the mark
floated up outside off and a firm punch gets past mid-off, nicely timed and gives the fielder a long chase back
short and down the leg side, ignored
pads up to a ball pitching outside leg stump
touch fuller and flicked through square leg
good length delivery well wide of off stump, Pietersen shoulders arms
touch fuller and straighter but left again
full delivery well wide of off stump, left again
bit of inswing here, tighter off stump line and Pietersen drives off low on the bat to extra cover
similar delivery patted back up past the bowler and they get an easy single
forward on off stump, blocked to extra cover
Lyon from around the wicket, Pietersen clips off the pads
Pietersen uses the feet and then takes it on the pad
turning too far down leg and KP is able to flick it away behind square leg
defends away to the off side
plenty of air from Lyon, this is defended easily though by Root
sharp turn now, he draws Root forward and gets past the bat, strikes Root on the pad
solidly defended to the off side
Pietersen pushes towards point with bat and pad close together
Pietersen leans forward to defend as Siddle keeps probing in that line just outside off
again Pietersen defends, trying to be patient
short of a length and Pietersen leaves this one alone
straighter ball to finish the over and Pietersen resists the temptation to flick through midwicket, where there are two catching men - he defends to off
turning in from around the wicket, Root flicks to leg
flighted and plenty of turn, Root lobs it off the thigh towards short leg
leans out to defend
goes right back on to his stumps to clip through square leg
around the wicket to Pietersen, who advances and drives along the ground towards short mid-on
advances again and flicks another one through square leg
Siddle keeps probing outside off, keeping things tight as KP leaves alone
solidly defended to the off side
left alone outside off
banged in short of a length and a touch straighter, Pietersen defends
on the back foot, Pietersen punches down the pitch
Pietersen goes for one this time, gets a strong cut away through point as Siddle continues to probe outside off, but just a fraction shorter
spinning down leg and Root moves with the spin to clip it forward of square leg
steps out of his crease to defend from off stump
rocks on to the back foot and punches through point this time, it is chased down inside the boundary
full toss gifts an opportunity for Root to pick up a boundary, and he does so, placing a drive through cover
touch short now and Root whippily works this forward of square leg
around the wicket to KP, who plays back and looks as if he's going to cut, then has to readjust when the ball turns too much, ugly flick back to the bowler in the end
yorker-ish delivery but it's outside off and a thick low edge bounces to second slip
straighter ball now at 142.1kph, Root defends
Root uses the angle across him and prods a gentle little drive through the gap at cover
banged in at the body, but just a touch too wide to really get at Pietersen, who tried to glance but there was much daylight between bat and ball
digs in in towards the hips again, Pietersen jumpily defends
bouncer, but too short to worry Pietersen - and in fact it's so high it's been called a wide
pushed across Pietersen, who leaves it alone
clipped through square leg for a couple as Johnson does the fielding on the boundary
worked away behind square leg for another one
nudged away defensively to leg
fuller and wider of off, Pietersen carefully pushes to point and can't find the gap
closes the face on one on the pads, just works it to midwicket
defended towards the off side
on the pads at 142.9kph and Root manages to glance this fine enough to pick up a boundary
146.6kph from Johnson as Root leaves alone outside off
'wait no!' is the call as Root goes on the back foot to punch to point

lovely placement from Root, he just waits on this one outside off and uses Johnson's pace to steer this behind point all the way along the ground, he's starting to look pretty comfortable at the crease
good line, just on off stump and Root defends
steered away to gully along the ground, Johnson is in the mid 140kph region here, not quite hitting the 150
angled in to the pads of Pietersen, who gets a thick inside edge onto the flap of the pad and this lobs up into the leg side - but safely
pushed away defensively to off
bat and pad close together as Root defends
some genuine swing now from Watson, coming in towards the pads and does hit Root on the leg, but it's moving too far
again Watson attacks the stumps - 136kph - and Root defends
swinging in again and Root goes back to defend
banged in short of a length and Pietersen defends off the back foot
flicked off the hips through midwicket for a single
angled across Root, who leaves one alone and this dies a bit as it goes through to Haddin
probes outside off at 147kph, Root just pushes calmly to the off side
beaten outside off now as Root plays inside the line, thinking this will come in more than it does
solidly defended once more
defends from middle and off
watchful, careful is Pietersen as he just leans a long way forward and defends
straight ball and Pietersen uses his wrists to close the face on this and work it to mid-on
straight-bat defence again
Watson continues to attack the stumps, Pietersen continues to defend
tailing in to the pads and Pietersen takes the opportunity to work this through midwicket, safely along the ground most of the way, but it is chased down inside the boundary
short to start with, a loosener, and Root pulls to deep midwicket
oh, what a lovely legbreak! Really tossed up and drifting in, then turns sharply away and beats Pietersen's edge - Haddin doesn't glove it
a crowd catch as Pietersen drives into the turf to short cover
outside off and turning further away, KP leaves it
straighter line now and Pietersen clips through midwicket
tossed up well above the eye-line and turns into a low full toss, which Root is happy to drive down towards mid-off for a single
turning down leg, Root leaves it alone
lovely ball, drifting across to pitch on off, turns back just enough and the thick inside edge onto pad lobs up but safely wide of bat-pad
clipped towards midwicket
too short now, which allows Root to swivel a pull to deep square leg
tossed up on the stumps, Pietersen leans out to defend
plenty of flight from Lyon, Pietersen drives to deep mid-on for a single
full delivery on off stump that Pietersen isn't totally forward to, gets a thick inside edge to midwicket
wider line and left well alone
full at the off stump, blocked back up the wicket
full onto off stump, blocked coming forward
slips this past the outside edge, it just left Pietersen enough, he was fiddling for it slightly outside off
full and wide and left alone
short and Root goes to pull down the leg side, it stops on him and takes the thigh pad to leg slip
thigh pad again via some turn to short leg this time
fuller length, kept out playing back in the crease
forward reach on off stump, pushed into the covers
floated up outside off, Root pushes in front of point and calls a sharp single, Pietersen is through but the thrown in from David Warner hits him on the arm
forward on the stumps, a polite enquiry for lbw but not particularly close
full length and some in-drift, Root plays forward and runs it out through midwicket
good length a foot and a half wide of off stump, left alone
touch shorter and Pietersen plays a nicely-timed back foot drive that is marvellously saved by a diving Chris Rogers at point
straighter line, Pietersen tries to play to leg and finds midwicket along the floor
short ball pulled without timing and gets a couple through midwicket
forward dropping this in front of point, loud cry of 'no' to possibly indicate that Pietersen didn't want a single
turn onto the pads going well down leg and high, no stroke offered
angled across Root who blocks forward around off stump
blocked in the crease, dropping it in front of short leg
four men around the bat, Root forward and edging through midwicket
a skip down the wicket and drive to extra cover
tossed up and flicked firmly to midwicket
full on the stumps, forward and nudged to midwicket
fuller ball nicely punched down the ground
short ball, Root under it early, has a smile about it too
a foot wide of off stump, ignored
full length wide of off stump, left alone
firm push forward and blocked to extra cover, solid
still around the wicket, off stump line, Pietersen backs away and cuts to point
first sign of aggression from Pietersen against the spinner, a silky stride down and whacks it through mid-off, good timing
down again and clipping to Lyon's right who saves well
forward pushing into the covers from off stump
flicked via short leg into the leg side for an easy single, playing with the spin
back on the stumps and tucking in front of short leg
full on off stump, blocked firmly into the covers
touch shorter in length and Pietersen can work this away from mid-off so they get a quick run
back of a length, Root up on his toes just outside off stump to push to point
forward just outside off and carefully ran into the gap at cover
short and Pietersen was in a position to hook but pulled out of the stroke
full ball that Pietersen plays slightly across to midwicket on the floor, decent set that from Harris
full and wide enough to whip the hands through and get a couple as point chases back, good running to get back for the second
forward on off stump playing on the bounce to silly point
slightly wider and Root reaches for it a bit, pushing up to mid-off
straighter line, blocked in front of the sticks
full on the stumps this time, knocked up the wicket with a bend of the front knee
flatter delivery, Root tickles it out to deep square leg
around the wicket and bowls on a length, Root blocks it in the crease
fuller delivery just outside off, Root forward blocking to cover
drops his length and Root gets up and knocks it towards point
blocked going back and across off stump
straighter line, tucked from the crease to midwicket
over the wicket, slides one full to just outside off, Root comes forward and dabs it towards point
step across the stumps and touched into midwicket
more air and whipped through midwicket for an easy single
tossed up into the rough outside off, Root comes right out to meet it and times a drive nicely through the covers
now short and pulled for four more, controlled stroke and finds the gap
nearly caught in two minds, ends up blocking in front of off stump
more flight, straighter line and turned with the spin behind square on the leg side
short of a length on off stump, Root up on his toes dabbing into the covers
bit meaner this, dug in and Root keeps it down from shoulder height
fuller ball slid across Root who leaves alone
full just outside off, driven quite sweetly but straight to extra cover
full and sliding across Root who feels for it and gets beaten, first mistake really and he'll be mighty relieved to have gotten away with it, Root smiles
short ball down the leg side, Root gets nicely inside it, Johnson has a word, Root again grins back at him
horrendous full bunger and Pietersen smashes it over long on, big strike that
that's better, decent length, Pietersen out to it kicking it away to the off side
floated up on leg stump, Pietersen with a giant stride forward playing in front of mid-on for a single
long hop pulled out to deep midwicket and the hundred comes up
plays around with mid-on again and takes a quick single having advanced down the track
back and pulled and the deep midwicket made a fabulous diving save, David Warner with a full-length slide to his left to save four and in fact just keeps them to one
sharp bumper that Root sharply gets underneath
fuller at the stumps, Root keeps it out with a straight bat
back of a length angled towards the off stump, Root punches to extra cover
slingy bumper, 93mph, got up very high and wasn't too threatening
full length that nearly sneaks past Root's forward push but he gets it through midwicket and goes to fifty, a nice little innings and proves to some extent that he can deal with No. 3
full wide one, a tempter that Root ignores
Pietersen charges and wasn't quite to the pitch, has to reach out for it and chips it over mid-off, bit of a let off for KP
more air, driven all along the floor to mid-off
forward just blocking in front of leg stump
back on his stumps and Smith did him for the length and beat Pietersen flirting outside off, close to the off stump too
now a full toss that Pietersen slaps to Warner who's a touch deep at mid-on so the single's on, Warner throws down the stumps but Pietersen is easily home
dragged down and pulled to the deep midwicket
full and wide and Root went for the drive and missed again, just being lulled into a few of these drives outside off, dangerous chasing them; more smiles
tighter line, Root casually runs it through cover and they take two
length delivery on off stump, blocked up the wicket
full on off stump and handily driven back past mid-off, not perfectly timed but a nicely nudged couple
bumper, right over the stumps, Root bounces down under it
around the wicket now, firm punch off the back foot and they get a couple more through the covers
long hop and pulled into the stands over midwicket, nicely timed and the hundred partnership is up, what a novelty
dragged down again and Pietersen pulls to mid-on off the toe
chance to go off side off the back foot now and finds deep cover
floated up on the stumps, played firmly to mid-on
back on the stumps and tucked against the turn into the vacant midwicket
tossed up on the stumps, whacked down the ground and Pietersen goes to fifty in fine style, another lovely strike
probing on off stump and it's defended
accurate again and Root defends
fuller length and Root drives to mid-off
fullish outside off and Root drives forward of point
not controlled this time as Siddle nips it in and it holds up off the pitch, the drive lobs wide of the catching midwicket
tries for the yorker but just not quite there and Pietersen clips through square leg uppishly
straight ball to begin with and it's defended with a straight bat
some inswing from Watson, Root defends
again it swings in a touch, Root is solid in defence
fullish and straight, it's prodded back to the bowler
this one swings a fraction the other way, but Root is happy to let it alone
driven back to the bowler
Siddle hits his usual line just outside off, it is defended once more
again Pietersen leans outside off to defend
left alone outside off, no swing for Siddle, unlike Watson
fuller and straighter, it's defended
too wide of off now to make Pietersen play
solid in defence once more
swinging in from outside off, but Root is happy leaving it alone
again Watson gets some movement in, again Root meets it with a straight bat
Watson is getting good movement and it's going a little both ways - this one curls away a touch and is left alone
banged in short and Root ducks underneath it
again this one straightens a bit and is left alone
clipped away to leg

gone! Siddle has made the breakthrough that Australia desperately needed, and it has come with an inside edge onto off stump. Siddle didn't nip it back much, but just enough, and it has caught the inside edge and Pietersen has played on. Huge breakthrough.
dismissed_batsman_text: KP Pietersen  b Siddle 53 (151m 99b 2x4 3x6) SR: 53.53

commentary_text: Bell drives to cover for his first ball, solid
steers it away to backward point
swinging in towards middle and leg, it's defended
pushed away defensively to backward point
left alone outside off
punched away off the back foot towards cover
Root is solid in defence once more as Watson probes outside off
fullish and straighter, Root drives towards mid-off
some good inswing here from wider of the crease, but it's far enough outside off that Root can leave it alone
Watson bends his back now, bangs in a bouncer at 136kph but it's far enough down leg that the batsman can evade it easily
probing on off, and it's defended
Siddle hits the right line just outside off, Bell puts the head down and defends
driven to cover, can't find a run to get off the mark
fullish from Siddle, Bell drives to the off sid
shortish but this one doesn't get up much, Bell tries the swivel pull but the ball sails past the bat and through to Haddin

Bell gets off the mark, but with a pretty tight single - he's pushed to backward point and taken off, thinking Harris the fielder wouldn't be quick - the throw missed at the striker's end and that may have been tight
defended back down the pitch
oooh, good ball to start as he angles it across and turns it back sharply, Bell leaves it alone but that didn't miss off stump by very much at all
again Bell leaves, this one doesn't turn back as much
left alone once more as Lyon probes outside off
beautiful shot, Bell rocks back as if to pull and then cuts hard, through cover point, lovely timing and placement
tossed up on middle and leg, Bell defends
plenty of flight this time, Bell leans out of his crease to defend
Siddle continues and finds his line just outside off, Root defends
solidly defended from middle and leg
steered away to backward point and Harris is very good, dives across to cut this off
swinging down leg and Haddin does well to dive across and collect this
again Siddle swings it down leg, wrong line, and Root is good enough to clip this off his pads through square leg, Lyon runs around from fine leg and knocks it on to the boundary with his dive
steered away through point
turning in to off stump from around the wicket, it's defended
clipped off the toes to square leg
tossed up by Lyon and the drive from Root doesn't really go anywhere
plenty of flight again, on middle and off and just straightening, it's defended
defended away to short leg
pushed away to midwicket
Bell goes back in his crease to cut to deep point
again on the back foot, Root this time forces through cover
advances and pads this away to the off side

Smith has struck! And he's done it with a full toss, what a disappointment for Bell! He has thrown it away. Smith lobs it up and this is a low fullie, there to hit but Bell has not got hold of it, all he has managed to do is chip it up to mid-on where - who else? - Mitchell Johnson runs a little to his right and takes a catch low to the ground
dismissed_batsman_text: IR Bell c Johnson b Smith 6 (28m 19b 1x4 0x6) SR: 31.57

commentary_text: Smith is around the wicket to the left-hander, he  tosses it up a lot, turns in sharply and lobs off the pad towards short leg

oooh, was that half a chance?! Not really - George Bailey would have to have done something incredible at short leg. Stokes went back and flicked a short one hard to leg, Bailey under the helmet tried to get out of the way and the ball has thumped him on the left hand.
defended away safely
Root steps back deep in his crease and defends
leans out of his crease to defend
again Root defends with a straight bat
flicked away to leg
low full toss and Root drives to mid-off
length ball, blocked from the crease to midwicket and they might have had a single but declined it
short and well wide of off stick
full and swinging in, there's the danger ball, Stokes tries to drive and gets a big inside edge into pad that lands in front of short leg
length ball on off stump, played forward and knocked into the gully
back of a length wide of off stump, left alone
now around the wicket, bowls a bumper which is easily ducked under
long hop pulled for four behind square
back and played up towards the bowler
forward on off stump and patted up the crease
fuller and blocked into the covers
another long hop, four more, just helped on it's way behind square on the leg side
blocked going back on leg stump, not a great over that
over the wicket, full down the leg side, superb diving take from Haddin
full length, beats the inside edge onto the knee roll, appeal for lbw, it was going down and he got a thin edge too, it spooned into the gully, did it carry? They don't review anyway
full on the stumps and Stokes plays a delightful straight drive, a confidence-booster that
length ball on off stump, Root dabs it down into the covers
full length just outside off, guided to point playing forward
short ball, Root sways inside the line, well played
length, turns away a bit, blocked in the crease just outside off
straighter and fuller, forward to block up the wicket
back to cut, it got away from him and it takes the toe in the end, short and wide of cover
better length and Stokes feels for it as it turns and beats him, well bowled
big stride in forward and blocks in front of off stick
back to cut again, this time nails it but short extra and then orthodox cover clean up
full length across Root who leaves alone
just back of a length, Root clips through midwicket off the stumps and they run hard to get back for the second
full and driveable just outside off, Root only finds mid-off who's quite close in
around the wicket, clipped with the angle through midwicket, they try for three but Bailey has done well
more off stump line, Root up on his toes taps it in front of the yellow-sunglassed Rogers and they take a quick single

full length, tails into off stump again, Stokes struck with bat and pad together, cry for lbw, not out given and Clarke reviews thinking this might be pad first. No-ball is tight but okay. And Stokes has smashed it onto his front pad so not the best review
down the track and gets a thick inside edge down the leg side that runs away for three, almost yorker himself their did Root
forward and tapped up the wicket
straight line, forward defence up the wicket
tossed up on off stump, Stokes forward and defending in front of silly point
more air, Stokes goes slightly across the line and clips to mid-on
tossed up nicely again, smothered on the crease
bumper down the leg side, Root stays inside the line
bumper, well-directed, Root gets right on top of the bounce around off stump, tucked out to point
full and wide and well ignored
chance to back foot drive and Root plays a blinder, fabulous timing and nails is through extra cover, wonderful technique there
short and down the leg side again
full and sliding past the off stump, Root lets it go by
touch short and Stokes cuts hard through extra cover, nicely put away
forward to a better-length ball and Stokes dabs it in front of silly point
floated up, smothered on off stump
forward just outside off and again knocked down in front of silly point
straighter and knocked back up the wicket coming forward
tossed up just outside off and left alone
good length ball on off stump, played with a dead straight bat
length delivery, just slides in a little and Root works it to midwicket
full delivery on off stump, Root forward playing back to the bowler
good length and Root gets a good stride in to defend
touch wider and back in length, Root punches off the back foot but only finds point
this time steers off the front foot ahead of Rogers and they run a quick single
turn down the leg side, Root touches it to backward square leg

straighter line, it turns in a little, Root was playing back and gets a little inside edge that runs off the pad and Haddin dives forward to take it and that is the breakthrough that Australia wanted. Root walks straight off, no century for him, but at least he's put up some kind of a fight. Little unlucky there but throughout the match fortune has favoured Australia and they've deserved their luck too. Good catch from Haddin diving forward
dismissed_batsman_text: JE Root c †Haddin b Lyon 87 (269m 194b 9x4 0x6) SR: 44.84

commentary_text: plays across the first ball and gets struck high on the pad
fends the next off to leg and almost gets caught at leg slip again
down the leg side, Prior leaves but thought about tickling it, no need
forward with a good stride knocking this back to Lyon
off stump on a length, blocked in the crease
