fuller and Stokes is very late on it, clips the pad outside the line I reckon, they go up for caught behind too, not out given but Clarke reviews again. I'm sure he didn't hit it, got beaten on the inside edge, the ball flicks the flap of the back pad and that it outside the line of off stump and missing, so not a great review at all. Second one burned.
straighter on a length, Stokes forward and defending this more solidly
fuller on the pads, Stokes goes to whip this to leg and misses
full at the off stump, a solid forward block
straight bat push up towards mid-on on the front foot
straight delivery, blocked in the crease
same delivery, knocked in front of short leg
floated up and flicked to midwicket
Prior unsure of his footwork, ends up poking at it in the crease and there's turn up onto the thigh pad
skips down and flicks to midwicket
Prior says enough is enough and runs down the wicket and belts it over mid-on, a right old leg side slap but he's off a pair
good length on off stump, Stokes is forward and running it back to the bowler
forward driving on off stump, there's a little inswing and it takes the inside edge to long leg
good length and it nibbles away and beats Prior playing away from his body
very full outside off and Prior leaves alone
angled in this, Prior comes forward a little and dabs to midwicket
full and wide of off stump, Prior leaves well alone
tossed up outside off and Stokes leaves well alone
fuller on leg stump, Stokes forward and runs it back up the wicket
same area, forward to block again
down the track and drives firmly, Lyon gets down with a left hand to save, good work
down he comes again but doesn't get to the pitch and just blocks
another sortie up the wicket, gently pushes to mid-off this time
wide on the crease, too wide of off stump too, Prior leaves
full and beats Prior outside off, didn't move his feet right out, played from the crease
straighter line, Prior plays on the walk and knocks it back to the bowler
length ball that's a little too straight and Prior tucks out to long leg
very full and Harris cries for lbw thinking again that it might be pad first in front of off stump, I think it was pad first but Australia are out of reviews and that would have been out
yorker length just outside off, Stokes digs it back to the bowler who shies at the stumps and throws miles past the keeper! Four overthrows for no reason at all!
'Lyno' still around the wicket, leg stump line, gets tucked to square leg
down the track and chips it over midwicket, this a more cultured stroke, well in control
forward on off stump and plays up the wicket
back of a length, blocked right back on his stumps
back defending in front of the timbers again
quicker ball and Prior needed to be alert to get across the off stump to block that
over the wicket, full on off stump, Stokes knocks it back up the wicket
wider line and Stokes able to easily leave alone
too wide to induce a stroke again
full at the pads, Stokes misses with a flick to leg
full at the pads again, Stokes misses with a flick to leg again, the ball rebounds to Johnson but no inside edge
length ball on off stump and blocked up the wicket again
wrong line and Prior tickles it to long leg
full length, just wide enough to leave and Stokes judges it well
straighter line, tucked from the crease to midwicket
driven just outside off, takes the inside edge again towards the leg side, hint of reverse again

you know what I was saying about Australia's luck being in, well this could be a catch off the boot of short leg, a flick to leg bounced up to Rogers at midwicket but the replay shows this to have hit the ground, that would have been a miserable way to get out
back foot punch aimed at the covers comes off a bottom edge into the ground
Johnson continues and Prior defends from outside off
nice shot from Prior, despite the shouts from the Australian fielders - he's opened the face and steered this down through gully and away to the boundary
Johnson skews this one a bit too wide of off, it is left alone
beaten outside off - Johnson at 141kph here - and Prior dabs at this and misses
Prior shoulders arms once again as Johnson just angles it across him
Johnson tries for the yorker but Prior keeps it out
Stokes tries to flick to leg but this lobs off the thigh pad towards short leg
Stokes defends down towards mid-on
probing on off stump and it is defended by Stokes
fullish on the stumps at 122kph as Siddle goes the slower one, Stokes drives to mid-on out of the middle of the bat
ouch! Bailey at short leg cops one on the leg as Stokes goes for the big hook and gets it down into the ground

Bailey in the action again! This is probably a dropped chance, if we're being hard on him. Very, very tough! Stokes whipped it hard off the legs and it hits Bailey in the midriff, then he can't quite get the hands under it. Split-second stuff there
around the wicket to Prior, who goes back deep to defend
tossed up on the stumps and it's defended again
flighted in towards leg and turning a little, it's defended
nudged away to leg
solid in defence as Lyon comes over the wicket now
Prior drives against the spin now, through cover and Warner manages to chase it down with a slide near the boundary
turning down leg and Stokes gets nothing on it
a lot of turn there from Smith from well wide of off but it's punched away to mid off
tossed up by Smith and Stokes goes for the sweep, gets the timing and placement just right and picks up a boundary through square leg
tossed up outside off, Stokes leans out to defend
really giving it a lot of flight and Stokes launches the big cover drive, this flies away through the gap for four
goes back to defend
Lyon turns it in from outside off, Prior goes back to defend
closes the face on this one and works it to mid-on
flighted outside off, Prior defends comfortably
watches the ball closely and goes back to defend
shouts of catch it as Prior works this to leg slip, but that was off thigh pad exclusively
driven on the bounce to cover, where Harris tumbles with all the grace of a felled tree to stop that
Smith getting plenty of turn but Stokes having little trouble, he just nudges it through square
73kph, slow and loopy, Stokes drives back to Smith
flighted again, driven to cover
flicked away through midwicket and finds a run
over the wicket to Prior, who watches it closely and goes back to defend outside off
fuller and down leg, Prior works a single through square leg
Prior defends watchfully
again he defends carefully outside off
Prior drives uppishly against the spin, but safely to point
drifting and turning, Prior gets out to defend with bat and pad close together
around the wicket now, Prior can't quite get this one away as it bounces a touch more
quicker and flatter, Prior defends
defended solidly by Stokes
on the pads and it's clipped down to fine leg
angled in to middle and leg, Prior defends
some nice curve away from the right-hander and plenty of carry to Haddin as Prior leaves it alone
square drive to point as Harris probes outside off
beaten outside off! Lovely ball from Harris, angles in and then swings away late, Prior's drive misses
just swinging down leg side, Stokes doesn't play
Johnson beats the bat now, good line and length at 146kph, draws Stokes into a tentative push outside off and this fizzes past the edge
defended from outside off stump, no real swing
Stokes defends really solidly outside off
no swing for Johnson and he bangs it in short of a length at 146kph, Stokes defends
left alone outside off
sharp bounce from Harris as this one nips away off the seam and Prior drags his bat inside it
swinging down leg and Prior flicks it to deep backward square
clipped away to the leg side safely
lovely on-drive, Stokes has played some nice shots but this is the best one yet, just times it to perfection, a punchy sort of drive that races away through mid-on
angled bat as he defends towards mid-off
Harris bangs it in short now and Stokes swivels a pull around the corner behind square
too far down leg side from Johnson, Stokes just watches this through to Haddin
bouncer this time, but Stokes can evade it comfortably
shortish again, Stokes watches carefully and leaves it
good one, just around chest height and angled across Stokes, who plays it well by leaving
over the wicket now is Johnson and Stokes glances fine

oh boy, this has not missed by much! Prior shoulders arms to a ball that is far too full. That seems a premeditated leave because that was one he should have been playing - only narrowly misses the off stump a few inches up from the ground
Harris gets his first of the match! He hits the right length that makes Stokes play on off stump but it nips away and the thick edge from Stokes is snapped up by Clarke at second slip
dismissed_batsman_text: BA Stokes c Clarke b Harris 28 (122m 90b 5x4 0x6) SR: 31.11

commentary_text: Broad clips it off the thigh and doesn't get off the mark, but does pick up a leg bye
solidly defended by Prior
angled in towards middle, Prior gets it away off a thickish inside edge
Broad gets on his toes to defend this down to short leg on the bounce
Broad is now off the mark with a quick single pushed to cover
beaten outside off! Oh, Broad prodded at this and missed, it has nipped away from him and not only just missed the bat, only narrowly missed off stump. Phew.
big swing now from Johnson, away from Broad but too wide and he drives comfortably through point

bouncer! This is what the crowd wanted from Johnson, he bangs it in short at 144kph and Broad doesn't get out of the way, he wears this on the shoulder! Also steps back deep into his crease - a hit wicket is half a chance here
flashes outside off and this beats the bat, lovely bowling
solid punch now though from Broad, through point
Johnson targets the stumps here with one swinging in but Broad manages to clip it to deep midwicket
Harris bangs it in short now but Broad evades it easily enough
good shot from Broad, gets one on the pads and flicks through midwicket, this runs away to the boundary
Broad nudges this towards cover
bouncer now and Broad tries to hook but is through the shot early, lobs off his shoulder to third slip but no bat involved there
uppish ... uppishly played! Broad prods it up to short cover on the bounce, he doesn't look comfortable at times
again Broad punches to cover, off the back foot
lovely shot! That's how to counter-attack, Broad lofts Harris over mid-off for a well-controlled four
Johnson angles it across Prior at 140.9kph, he drives towards cover
straight-bat defence from Prior as Johnson goes short of a length now
here's a chance, is it? No, not quite - Prior has swivel pulled this but off the top edge, and it flies high and out towards square leg, but not far enough to reach Lyon on the full
147.7kph and short! Broad folds himself up like a nervous baby giraffe, gets underneath it. I dunno if baby giraffes fold themselves up to avoid dangers but that's what he looked like.
clipped off the hip, lobs up wide of short leg
cuts hard and high over the cordon, this bounces safely down at third man
beats Broad outside off with one that really grips and turns
a touch shorter and Broad crunches a boundary through cover point, well played
turns away from the rough outside off, left alone
punched off the back foot through cover
half a chance maybe? Prior works this off the legs and Watson at leg slip dives to his right but can't quite get to it - definitely off the bat but Watson couldn't get a hand to it
left alone outside off
Prior watches this closely and leaves outside off
Prior gets back in his crease to defend
short ball and Prior wants to have a go at this, pulls hard and forward of midwicket, gets this away safely through the big gap
four more for Prior, he is playing his shots all of a sudden, hooks another short one and it flies off the top edge over Haddin's head
Prior goes back on his stumps to defend
angled across Prior at 147.9kph, he leaves it alone
back of a length on leg stump, clipped down to long leg
wide of off stump and left alone
drops his length and bowls a straighter line, gets clipped out to long leg
short and pulled, there are two men back but Broad has whacked this straight into the pavilion!

hooked again and this time Broad puts it right down deep square leg's throat how awfully typical for this batting performance. That is an utter miserable stroke. Banged in again and Broad falls for it hook, line and sinker, slogging it straight to Lyon who barely has to move coming in from the rope. Pretty pathetic that from Broad
dismissed_batsman_text: SCJ Broad c Lyon b Siddle 29 (32m 26b 3x4 1x6) SR: 111.53

commentary_text: back of a length on off stump and Swann blocks it getting up on his toes
back foot drive through point, absolutely gorgeous timing, sweet as you like that
drives off the front foot this time and carves it to backward point
short and straight and pulled through midwicket, nicely timed again, is Prior finding some form here
a better bumper and Prior pulls out of the short ball
length on middle and off, Prior blocks in the crease
short again and Prior was trying to uppercut but missed as the ball went over middle
bumper, well directed, ducked
forcing shot from the crease through the covers
forced again into the covers and they take a quick single
full in towards the off stump and eased through the covers, not timed, they get a couple more
played into the covers again, timed pretty well here but straight to cover point
straighter line, Prior is forward and playing to midwicket
bumper, well, directed, Swann lets it go but it's deemed too high
fuller on off stump, pushed carefully through mid-off
full ball outside off, Prior leans out and steers it wide of third man for a couple
short and pulled in front of midwicket, well struck and four more
fuller sliding across Prior, he felt for it without moving his feet and got beaten, false stroke
full slid across Prior again, he swings at it, yet again without moving his feet, and plays and misses again, getting closer is Johnno
this time he nails the drive but George Bailey gets down with a superb save to his right, more fine fielding from Australia
forward just outside off, ran into the gully
short at the body, pulled hard all along the ground out to deep square leg
full at off stump, Prior drives without timing into the covers
pulled again in front of square, timed well, and Prior goes to fifty, what a badly-needed innings this is for England
back of a length, pulled again, along the ground to deep square leg
bumper, Swann stays inside the line and it goes through to Brad Haddin
straight on a good length, Prior blocks it up the wicket
a flashing square drive to a full ball wide of off stump, finds point who is quite deep
full at the leg stump, slower this at 80mph, tucked to midwicket
fuller length, back up at 88mph, blocked in front of middle and off
slash at a good length ball offering a little width, finds point
another slash at a ball sliding across the off stump, takes a big top edge but safe enough and evades third man
full length, two feet wide of off stump, left alone
full delivery tighter to off stump, Prior blocks it up the wicket
good length on off stump, Swann forward and pressed into the covers
short outside off, Swann fetches it across to deep square leg with a controlled stroke
oh delicious, a flowing on-drive, absolutely perfect timing and it sails down the ground
back of a length outside off, Prior uppercuts but doesn't get all of it, Warner is interested running back from backward point but can't get there, just enough willow on it from Prior
full on the stumps, Prior pushes it through midwicket
full ball wide of off stump, Swann shoulders arms

back of a length outside off, Swann pushes hard at it away from his body with a nothing stroke and gets a thick edge to second slip where Clarke bags an easy catch at shoulder height with two hands. The delivery shaped away a touch but started too wide to induce a stroke. Chalk it up as another poor dismissal
dismissed_batsman_text: GP Swann c Clarke b Harris 6 (32m 14b 0x4 0x6) SR: 42.85

commentary_text: Anderson on a king pair, gets in behind this on off stump and blocks
full at the stumps from around the wicket, Anderson whips with the angle and finds long leg, gets off a pair too
more superb timing, a decent length only a foot outside off, Prior stays leg side and uses the pace to steer it wide of third man
down the leg side, Anderson watches it past him
similar delivery but this time Anderson flicks at it and steers it through square leg
just back of a length outside off, Prior slaps it through cover and - wait for it - the 300 comes up!
short ball that Prior tries to pull, it isn't as quick as Prior was thinking and he's through with the shot too soon

short and hooked again and, well, well, well can you Adam and Eve it, picks out deep-backward square leg. England, deary me. Harris the catcher this time. There's no point describing the wicket because you know the drill by now surely
dismissed_batsman_text: MJ Prior c Harris b Siddle 69 (153m 102b 12x4 0x6) SR: 67.64

commentary_text: short ball and PANESAR HOOKS TO DEEP SQUARE!! No just joking, that would be the final straw for humanity if he was that silly. He ducks
around the wicket, down leg side, ignored
bumper, well directed, ducked
angled in, Anderson hit on the thigh pad as he looks to flick into the leg side
good length just outside off and Anderson unleashes a lofted straight drive. Didn't quite time it but a decent thump nevertheless
short and ducked yet again
another shortie, Panesar under it easily
back of a length at the body, Anderson manages to fend it down in front of gully
excellent short ball, bit higher and straighter and Anderson knows little about it, throwing the gloves up to it and punches it down to fine leg
another short delivery, blocked on top of the bounce in front of off stump
full length outside off, Anderson swings from the crease and gets enough bat on it through mid-on to collect four, quite an ungainly swing but four nevertheless
back of a length again, Anderson pulls, is through with the shot too soon and wears it under the armpit
you know where it's pitched, Anderson tries to stay leg side and cut but gets a bottom edge to gully
full on off stump, Panesar forwards and drives into the covers
straighter line, Panesar from the crease plays forward and gets an inside edge to square leg
good length on off stump and Panesar plays a fine-looking straight drive that Harris saves well

length outside off and Panesar slaps it to short extra-cover and Australia have wrapped up a 218 run victory to go 2-0 up in the series. Panesar can't add the resistance of the first innings to the second dig, got a driven off the toe and it was simply pouched by Rogers at hip height
dismissed_batsman_text: MS Panesar c Rogers b Harris 0 (13m 7b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00
